title: mayo biscuits
directions: Mix well and drop into a greased muffin pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: dirt cake
directions: You also need one 10-inch pot (may substitute other type of container instead).

title: sausage and rice dressing
directions: Cook rice mix according to package directions.
Set aside.
In a skillet melt butter.
Saute the onion and celery until tender. Combine all remaining ingredients and place in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Combine all ingredients. Beat 2 minutes and bake according to package directions.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburg and onions in Dutch oven.
Add the other ingredients and simmer.

title: cheese ball with chopped beef
directions: Mix together and roll in chopped nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: stuffed eggs with crabmeat
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove yolks and mash. Combine with crabmeat, celery, green pepper, salad dressing mix and sour cream.
Blend well.
Refill eggs.
Chill and serve.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together.
Pack gallon glass jar with pickles (be sure you clean them real good), 5 heads of dill and 6 toes of garlic.
Add 1/2 teaspoon alum.

title: thumbprints
directions: Mix ingredients together; roll into balls.
Dip in slightly beaten egg white.
Roll in finely chopped nuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 5 minutes at 375°.
Remove from oven; press thumb into the middle of cookie ball.
Return to oven for 8 more minutes.
Fill with jelly when done.

title: tuna dinner
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese dinner as directed on box.
Stir in soup and mix.
Gently stir in tuna.
Heat to serving temperature.

title: blueberry nut crunch
directions: Spread pineapple over bottom of lightly greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Toss together blueberries, half of sugar and lemon juice in a bowl.
Layer over pineapple.
Sprinkle cake mix over top of fruit layers.
Dribble melted butter or margarine on top of cake mix.
Sprinkle on chopped pecans and other half of sugar.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
After it has baked 20 minutes, cut through to bottom of pan to let juices rise to the top.
Serves 12.
Best served warm.

title: punch
directions: Mix lemonade, sugar and water.
Add ginger ale or 7-Up just before serving.
Make molds of fruit punch and Kool-Aid (not adding as much water).

title: custard cake
directions: Mix sugar and shortening, then beat in eggs and vanilla, then add dry ingredients and milk.
Beat at medium speed of mixer for 5 minutes.
Bake 30 or 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: clam casserole
directions: Add all ingredients to beaten eggs. Put in 2-quart casserole, greased. Set dish in a pan with 1-inch of water. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green bean caesar
directions: Cook and drain beans.
Toss beans with salad oil, vinegar, oil, salt, pepper and garlic.
Pour into ungreased 1-quart casserole.
Stir together bread crumbs, cheese and oleo. Sprinkle over beans.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: calico baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Fry bacon almost crisp; drain.
Fry onion until tender.
Combine hamburger, bacon, onion, brown sugar, catsup, vinegar, dry mustard and beans into casserole dish. Cover.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Stir and bake uncovered for an additional 45 minutes.
Do not drain any of the beans.

title: helen fetsko cold dough
directions: Cut flour and oleo together like you do for a pie crust until it is a fine mixture. Add beaten egg yolks and sour cream. Knead well to form a large ball and hands are clean.
You may need to add a little flour if dough is sticky. Use as little as possible. Divide dough into 4 small rolls.
Cover with Saran Wrap; place in refrigerator 3 to 4 hours or overnight.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press dough into a pizza pan (12 to 14-inch).
Bake about 10 minutes at 350° until lightly browned. Combine cream cheese, condensed milk, lemon juice and vanilla. Spread on cooled crust.
Chill.
Pour strawberry glaze over cooled cream cheese mixture.
Arrange strawberries and/or other fruit over this.

title: best blueberry muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line 12 muffin cups or grease with shortening.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, whisk eggs, milk and margarine; add to flour mixture, stirring until just moistened.
Fold in blueberries.
Spoon evenly into muffin cups.
Sprinkle with sugar. Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
(Can be frozen up to 1 month.
Reheat in microwave on defrost for 2 1/2 minutes.)
Makes 12 large muffins.

title: congealed salad
directions: Soften cream cheese at room temperature.
Dissolve cream cheese and jello in boiling water.
Add milk, pineapple and nuts. Pour in greased mold or container and chill 8 to 12 hours.

title: swiss steak
directions: Sprinkle meat with pepper, meat tenderizer and then flour.
Fry until lightly browned on medium-high heat.
Place cooked meat in a large casserole dish.
Layer onions, celery and carrots over meat. Then pour tomato sauce over all.
Bake at 250° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Serve with mashed potatoes, cooked peas and hot rolls.

title: chicken teriyaki
directions: Stir soy sauce, ketchup, white wine, sugar and garlic in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Marinate chicken 1 hour on each side.
Bake in marinade at 400° for 1 hour, turning once after first 30 minutes.

title: easy kutya(ukrainian christmas dish)
directions: Rinse wheat in sieve; drain.
Put in 2-quart pot and cover with water about 2-inches above wheat.
Cook on medium heat until boiling; reduce heat and semi-cover.
Let cook for about 2 hours. Do not drain water.
After cooking, take off heat and let stand. (Check to see if water evaporated during cooking time; if so, add some hot water to the wheat during cooking time to prevent wheat from clumping.)
Let cool.

title: sourdough pancakes
directions: Mix good.
Drop 1/4 cup on hot grill that's sprayed with Pam. Will make about 12 medium pancakes.

title: vanilla wafer pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream butter and sugar in a bowl.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Add milk and wafer crumbs, mixing well. Stir in coconut, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cream cheese and 2 tablespoons margarine until smooth.
Add next 6 ingredients and mix well (chicken, salt, pepper, milk, onion and pimento).
Can also add chopped celery.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles.
Firmly press perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/4 of chicken mix onto center of each rectangle.
Pull the 4 corners to the top of mixture.
Twist slightly and seal edges.
Brush tops with 1 tablespoon margarine. Sprinkle with crouton crumbs.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden.

title: vegetable bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cook broccoli as directed on package except just until heated through.
Drain.
Mix broccoli and process cheese spread.
Spoon into greased 10 x 6-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with crumbs and dot with margarine.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: stuffed spud soup
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add soup, milk, half and half and thawed potatoes. Stir in cheese and heat gently.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Combine butter and oil and melt marshmallows in this mixture. Remove from heat, mix in popcorn and M&M's and place in a greased tube pan.
Allow to cool for 1 hour; turn out of pan.
Do not refrigerate.
Serves 12.

title: baked apples(crock-pot)
directions: Wash and core apples.
Mix raisins and sugar and fill center of apples.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and dot with butter.
Place in a crock-pot.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Cover and cook on low 8 hours (high 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 hours).

title: nana jaspers lasagna
directions: Brown ground round with onions and garlic; drain well. Add tomatoes, paste, water, salt and sugar; simmer about 1 hour. Mix cheeses together and boil noodles. Layer alternately noodles, cheese and meat sauce, ending with meat sauce. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly (can cover the first 20 minutes with aluminum foil to prevent lasagna from drying out).

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Mix the cinnamon and sugar in medium-size bowl.
Add a few pieces of biscuits at a time to sugar mixture and stir to coat.
Place a layer of pieces in a greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle with pecans, raisins or coconut.
Place layers until all biscuit pieces are in pan.
Sprinkle remaining cinnamon and sugar mix over last layer.
Boil the brown sugar and butter.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.
Invert on plate.

title: cheese grits
directions: Prepare grits according to the directions on the package. Remove cooked grits from heat and add the next 5 ingredients. Stir until cheeses and butter melt.
Slowly add the mixture to the beaten eggs.
Pour into a 9-inch ungreased baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Garnish with fresh herbs: parsley or rosemary make a lovely presentation.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
This recipe doubles very well.

title: yeast loaf bread
directions: Combine water, yeast, sugar, shortening and salt.
Stir until yeast dissolves.
Add flour and mix well.
Turn onto floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic.
Cover with warm, damp cloth and allow to rise until double in bulk.
Punch down and form into two loaves.

title: lumberjack bean bake
directions: Fry bacon and onion just until onion is tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in sugar, vinegar, salt, mustard and garlic salt; simmer, covered, 15 minutes.
In a large 4-quart casserole, combine the 4 kinds of beans; toss lightly to mix.
Spoon bacon mixture over top of beans.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbly.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: ham spread
directions: Blend together in food processor.
Serve with crackers or great for finger sandwiches.

title: sage meat loaf
directions: Combine eggs and milk; stir in the bread crumbs, onion, parsley, salt and sage.
Add beef; mix well.
Pat mixture into an 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan and bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Spoon off the excess fat.
Combine the ketchup, brown sugar and dry mustard; spread over the meat loaf and return to the oven for an additional 10 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Cook, drain and cool macaroni.
Place in bowl.
Add salad dressing and Salad Supreme.
Add rest of ingredients; mix well and chill.
Better if made the night before.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans by directions on bag.
Place beans, onion, bell pepper, garlic, sausage and enough water to fill pot about halfway.
Cook slowly for three to four hours, stirring often. Add remaining ingredients and cook until beans are tender.
You may need to add water as necessary to keep beans from sticking. After beans have become tender, let the water cook down to sauce consistency.
This may be prepared in advance and is better the second day.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Add 3/4 cup boiling water to Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved. Add cold Coca-Cola and stir.
Add pineapple, cherries and pecans. Mix thoroughly.
Top with marshmallows.
Chill until set.

title: lavender bath mix
directions: Simmer together in a pan of water with tightly fitting lid for an hour.
Strain and add to bath water for a luxurious bath.

title: chicken dressing casserole(great depression dressing)
directions: Boil chicken on stove top with carrots, celery and onions until done.
Make stuffing as directed on box.
Mix the 2 cans of soup with 1 can of water.
In 2-quart casserole dish, layer one part soup mix in bottom of dish, then chicken, then dressing.
Top with remaining soup.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 10 to 15 minutes.

title: favorite coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease round or square layer pan.
Blend all ingredients, except topping; beat vigorously for 1 minute. Spread in pan.
Sprinkle topping over batter.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: shrimp mousse
directions: Heat soup; dissolve softened cheese in it.
Soak gelatin in cold water; dissolve in hot cheese mixture.
Let cool 30 minutes. Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a mold and chill.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: buttery rolls
directions: Scald milk; add butter, sugar and salt, stirring until butter melts.
Let mixture cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in water in a large bowl.
Add milk mixture, eggs and 2 cups flour; beat at low speed of an electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Turn dough out onto a floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic (about 8 to 10 minutes).
Place in a well-greased bowl, turning to grease top. Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.
Roll dough 1/2-inch.
Cut with biscuit cutter dipped in melted butter.
Fold over.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until browned.
Brush rolls with melted butter. Yield:
2 dozen.

title: black forest cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan or 3 (9-inch pans).
Beat eggs and oil.
Add cake mix and fold in pie filling.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake until toothpick comes out clean, 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool on rack before frosting with chocolate icing made with last five ingredients.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine sour cream, soup, small can of sliced black olives and the diced chilies.
Put a spoonful of the mixture, grated cheese and chicken on a tortilla.
Roll up and put into a pan.
Pour remaining sour cream mixture over tortillas.
Top with grated cheese and garnish with olives.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve with salsa and guacamole.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Combine all ingredients in a serving bowl, mixing thoroughly with sour cream.
Chill overnight, if possible.
Serve cold as is.

title: turkey sausage strata
directions: Spray 13 x 9-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. Layer bread, Mozzarella cheese, sausage, onion, broccoli and pimento in baking dish.
In medium bowl, combine egg product, milk, salt and mustard; blend well.
Pour over sausage mixture; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight.
Heat oven to 325°.
Uncover; bake at 325° for 55 to 70 minutes or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 12 servings.

title: eleanor's lemon salad
directions: Mix together in order given and chill.

title: spice cookies
directions: Sift flour with baking soda, cloves, allspice, cinnamon and ginger on sheet of waxed paper.
In medium bowl with electric mixer, beat butter, sugar and egg until light and fluffy.
With wooden spoon, beat in flour mixture alternately with molasses. Beat well after each addition.
Refrigerate dough, covered, 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet. Shape dough into 1/2-inch balls. Roll in confectioners sugar.
Place on cookie sheet 1-inch apart. Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Remove to rack. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar while still warm.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook the spaghetti, oil and salt according to directions on package.
Drain and add the Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Arrange like a crust in a large pie pan.
Put your favorite meat and sauce in center.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup of boiling water.
Dissolve cranberry sauce, separating berries.
Mix all other ingredients into this mixture; chill until congealed.
This is very colorful when prepared in a clear baking dish.
Yields 12 servings.

title: chicken wild rice salad
directions: Cook and cool rice.
Add onions, chicken, green peppers, pimento, celery and salt to rice.
Mix mayonnaise, Russian dressing and lemon juice.
Add to chicken and rice mixture. Refrigerate overnight.

title: bread pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, cream sugar, butter and eggs.
In another bowl, break up cinnamon rolls.
Mix cream (milk), vanilla and raisins with egg mixture.
Pour this in bread (cinnamon rolls) and let set about 10 minutes.
Mix thoroughly after. Lightly butter 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan or equivalent size and pour bread mixture into pan.
Smooth top.
Bake in 350° oven until set. It need not be firm; bake about 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm with Lemon or Rum Sauce.

title: shipwreck
directions: Spray or grease pan.
Place layer of potatoes, layer of beef, layer of corn, then pour diluted soup over top.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add other ingredients and nuts. Shape into small 1-inch balls.
Place in greased cookie sheet. Bake 15 minutes at 300°.
Roll in confectioners sugar while still hot.

title: pineapple pilaf
directions: Heat butter in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add onions, walnuts, raisins, salt and ginger.
Cook, stirring 4 to 5 minutes or until onions are tender.
Add rice and pineapple.
Stir and heat thoroughly.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook well and drain the squash, onion and carrots.
Mix 1 can cream of chicken soup with sour cream and pimientos.
Mix stuffing mix with stick of melted margarine (may use more margarine). Press half of stuffing to the bottom and sides of casserole dish. Add squash mixture.
Put remaining half of stuffing on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (approximately).

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Put peanut butter and butter on low heat.
Bring sugar, water and syrup to soft ball stage.
Beat egg whites until stiff, then add 1/2 of sugar mixture.
Return sugar mixture to boil; let mixture get to hard ball stage.
Pour into egg whites and beat. Add vanilla.
Pour sugar and egg mixture on powdered sugar and roll out.
Spread peanut butter on the rolled out sugar mixture. Roll up and slice.

title: easy eggnog pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, combine cake mix, Borden's eggnog and oil.
Beat on low speed until moistened. Add eggs and nutmeg; beat on medium-high speed 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch fluted or tube pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar, if desired.

title: glorified gingerbread
directions: Crumb together flour, sugar and shortening; set aside 1/2 cup of the crumbs.
Add to the rest of the crumbs the baking molasses, egg, sour milk, ginger, cinnamon and salt.
Lastly, add soda dissolved in hot water.
Pour in baking pan.
Sprinkle the 1/2 cup reserved crumbs on top and bake at 350° until done.

title: tagliarini
directions: Cook noodles; brown beef and saute onion, garlic and peppers until tender.
Mix all ingredients together in large casserole dish.
Sprinkle some of the cheese on top.
Heat at 350° until cheese melts.

title: bacon and egg salad
directions: Chop eggs and bacon together. Add salt, mustard and mayo. Mix well. Total carbs: 8.6 for whole recipe.

title: prune bread
directions: Sift flour with spices, soda and salt.
Set to one side.
Stir oil and sugar together; add eggs, one at a time and mix well.
Add sour milk or buttermilk to oil, sugar and egg mixture.
Add sifted flour to egg mixture, then prunes and nuts.
Bake in a greased loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
If you like frosting, rum flavored butter icing is perfect.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Arrange asparagus, cheese and pimiento in layers in casserole dish.
Spread soup evenly and top with cracker crumbs. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: beef spread
directions: Dice dried beef into 1/4-inch squares (approximately).
Mix with other ingredients.
Be sure to have cream cheese and sour cream at room temperature for best results while mixing.
Pack in Christmas jars, sour cream container, Tupperware, etc. Refrigerate.
Great on sesame seed or other snack crackers.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 8 x 10-inch pan.
Add oatmeal to boiling water and set aside for about 20 minutes. Combine remaining ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well and add oatmeal.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Top with broiled topping.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: In large heavy saucepan, combine sugar with corn syrup, butter and salt.
Bring to boiling over low heat, stirring until butter melts and sugar is dissolved.
Add pecans.
Reduce heat.
Add sweet potatoes, arranging in single layer.
Baste well with syrup. Cook, covered, over a low heat, turning once in 15 minutes. Remove cover.
Cook, basting occasionally, 15 minutes longer or until potatoes are well glazed.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
In mixer bowl combine all items except pie shell and mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or when knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Cool.
Garnish as desired or serve plain.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: rob roy cookies
directions: Combine brown sugar, salt, spices, milk and eggs.
Beat thoroughly.
Sift flour and soda.
Add to other mixture.
Add oats, nuts and raisins.
Drop onto pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: spaghetti spinners(good for kids)
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Mix and coat spaghetti well.
Use a nonstick or lightly greased, foil-lined cookie sheet.
Take a fork full of spaghetti mixture and spin on cookie sheet creating a coil of strands.
Each coil can vary from 2 to 3 inches.
Bake at 400° for 3 to 4 minutes until rigid. Remove from oven and when each is slightly warm or use spinners in tomato or vegetable soups.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix with Ranch dressing.

title: hash brown bake
directions: Stir ingredients together, and spread in a 9x12 pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle 2 cups crushed potato chips over mixture.
Melt 1 stick oleo, and pour over chips.
Bake another 15 minutes.

title: butternut squash casserole
directions: Combine the above ingredients and place in a buttered casserole. Top with cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bake at 350° until brown, 45 minutes.
Yields 1 small casserole.

title: mock boursin cheese ball
directions: Blend all ingredients with a fork.
Form into a ball.
Serve with crackers.
You can made a day ahead and can even freeze it.

title: mother's banana bread
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add milk/soda mixture alternately with flour.
Mix all and then add mashed bananas and vanilla, mixing well.
Pour into ungreased angel food cake pan and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Let cool and then remove from cake pan.
Enjoy!!
Can be made and baked in muffin cups for 20 minutes at 350°.
Great to serve at breakfast or to take to work for coffee break!!

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla until smooth and creamy.
Add mashed pumpkin; stir well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and baking soda; add spices.
Mix well.
Add raisins and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° about 10 minutes.
They will not be browned on top.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Cook hamburger and sausage in a skillet until done; drain. Add cheese to meat mixture and heat until cheese is melted. Mix well. Spoon 1 teaspoon of meat and cheese mixture on party rye bread. Place under broiler until bread is crispy. Great as an appetizer.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll out cookie dough into 1 piece to fit on a round pizza pan.
Bake 8 to 15 minutes or until firm. Cool and spread with cream cheese.
Arrange fruit in concentric circles.
Slightly warm orange marmalade and brush over fruit. Serve immediately

title: chocolatey peanut butter fudge
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in microwave bowl.
Microwave for about 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir until all chips are melted.
Add peanuts.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Refrigerate until set.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Combine the 3 ingredients and place in ice cream freezer. Makes about 1 gallon frozen dessert.

title: taco dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In shallow 1-quart casserole, combine soup mix, sour cream, cream cheese, ground beef and 1/2 cup shredded cheese.
Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup cheese over top. Bake 30 minutes or until heated through.
Top with lettuce and tomato.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: hot onion sauce for leftover meats
directions: Slice onions thin and saute in butter (using heavy skillet) about 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with flour.
Stir mixture 2 to 3 minutes.
Stirring, add vinegar to make thin creamy sauce.
Bring sauce to boil and simmer about 20 minutes.
Using ovenproof dish, arrange meat in overlapping slices over layer of sauce and covering with balance of sauce.
Bake, covered, for a half hour at 350°.
Use over rice or noodles.

title: festive turkey salad
directions: Gently toss first 8 ingredients together.
Season to taste. Pour salad mixture onto a bed of romaine leaves and garnish with slivered almonds.
Chill for at least one hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and margarine together.
Press on bottom of 9 x 13-inch dish.
Blend and mix cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour over cake mixture and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: german struddle
directions: Mix the above add enough flour to make a stiff dough. knead well.
Cover and let rest for 1 hour.
Divide the dough into 2 balls.
Roll out as thin as possible.
Spread with melted butter and and saute onions.
Stretch and then roll up, cut into 2 inch pieces.
Put on top of meat like ribs or steak.
Cover and steam for 45 minutes.
This is a complete meal.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add broccoli and water.
Cook until tender.
Then add soup, Cheez Whiz and rice.
Mix all together and let stand 5 minutes.
Pour into greased casserole and bake, covered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: rosy potato soup
directions: In a large saucepan, saute onion and celery in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour and salt until blended.
Gradually add milk.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened and bubbly.
Reduce heat.
Add potatoes, parsley and paprika; heat through. Yield: 5 servings.

title: maple fruit and nut bread
directions: Cover apricots with boiling water.
Let stand 15 minutes. Drain and chop.
Mix apricots, dates and nuts.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add brown sugar and date mixture; mix.
Combine egg and milk; add maple syrup and stir into dry ingredients.
Pour into 2 well-greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Let stand 15 to 20 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°; bake about 50 minutes.
Cool on a rack.

title: gulliver's corn
directions: Cook together corn, cream, salt and sugar for 10 minutes. Melt oleo and add flour; mix well.
Pour into corn mixture.

title: scallops in bacon
directions: Cut large scallops in half.
Wrap each scallop in 1/2 strip of bacon.
Secure with toothpick.
Sprinkle teriyaki sauce over all. Place in baking dish and bake at 425°, turning once for 20 to 30 minutes or until done.
Serve with sweet-and-sour sauce.

title: cat leveen's meat loaf
directions: In a large mixing bowl place bread slices.
Pour canned milk over bread and let set until soft enough to crumble.
Add ground beef and all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into loaf. Place into baking dish.
Pour 1/2 cup water around loaf.
Bake in 350° oven 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until brown.

title: seven cup salad
directions: Drain all of the fruit and then just mix everything together and let sit a few hours in refrigerator.

title: homemade lemonade
directions: Juice lemons enough for 1 cup juice, reserving rinds.
Combine juice, rinds and 3 1/2 cups water in glass container.
Cover and set in sun for 4 hours.
Remove rinds.
Add sugar syrup to taste and chill.
Just before serving, add slices to pitcher and serve over ice.
Makes 1 quart.

title: frank and kraut stew
directions: In Dutch oven, cook onion in margarine until tender. Add sauerkraut, tomatoes, potatoes, carrots, water, sugar, bouillon cube, salt and pepper. Simmer, covered, until tender, about 45 minutes. Stir occasionally. Add frankfurters.
Simmer, covered, about 5 minutes.
Makes 9 or 10 servings.

title: macaroni pie
directions: Cook macaroni but not mushy, then drain.
Add 3/4 of the grated cheese and butter.
Stir until melted.
Beat eggs and add milk.
Stir this in the macaroni mixture.
Put in a glass dish that has been greased or sprayed with Pam.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sesame pork tenderloin
directions: Marinate pork in ingredients 8 hours or overnight.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender, drain and add butter. Chop carrot, onion and pepper in blender and drain.
Mix all ingredients and pour into casserole dish; sprinkle a handful of stuffing mix and Parmesan cheese over top. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until bubbly all over.

title: fruit cake with starter
directions: Mix and stir once a day for 10 days. On 10th day, add 2 1/2 cups sugar and 1 (No. 2) can pineapple with juice (I use chunks). Stir once a day for 10 days.
On 20th day, add 2 1/2 cups sugar, 1 (17 ounce) can fruit cocktail with juice and 1 cup sliced maraschino cherries.
On 30th day, drain liquid from fruit and divide into 4 or 5 jars, 1 1/2 cups each.
Divide fruit into 3 thirds.
This makes 3 cakes.

title: stuffing
directions: Cook onion in skillet with butter until onion is transparent. Set aside.
Put cubed bread in a casserole bowl and sprinkle sage and poultry seasoning over top.
Mix.
(Don't overspice.)
Now, pour onions and butter over top and mix.
Pour milk over top to moisten and put in oven for 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: brown sugar fudge
directions: Combine sugars, milk and salt in a saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils rapidly, 239° or until a firm ball is formed in cold water.
Remove from heat; set saucepan in cold water to cool.
Place butter on top of fudge without stirring; coat top with butter to prevent fudge from sugaring.
Cool to lukewarm; add vanilla and nuts.
When cool, beat and pour into buttered square pan; cut into squares.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk.
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips. Add marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken broccoli bake
directions: In buttered 9-inch square baking dish, layer broccoli, chicken, bread cubes and cheese.
In medium bowl, combine gravy, milk and pepper; pour over chicken-broccoli mixture.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: dump salad
directions: Dump ingredients together and mix in large bowl.
Chill overnight before serving.

title: party punch
directions: Mix all ingredients (except the ginger ale) in a gallon container, then freeze.
Thaw about 3 to 4 hours before serving. It should be mushy.
Add ginger ale and serve without additional ice.
Makes about 60 cups.

title: apple dessert
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and press in bottom of 8 x 10-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Peel and slice apples.
Combine sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Stir into apple slices until well coated.
Arrange apple slices in pan.
Sprinkle leftover sugar mixture over apples.
Bake at 350° for about 60 minutes or until apples are done.
Remove from oven.
Prepare 1 package instant vanilla pudding and pour over hot apples. Refrigerate.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: okra
directions: Using an ovenware dish, layer 1/2 each.
Sprinkle water over top of all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: country-style chicken kiev
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cheese, basil, oregano, salt and garlic salt. Dip chicken pieces in butter. Set remaining butter aside. Roll chicken in bread crumbs.
Place chicken, skin up, in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes. To leftover butter, add wine, onion and parsley.
Pour over baked chicken. Bake 2 to 3 minutes more.

title: play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Stir in water and oil and knead.
May be colored with food coloring.
Store in airtight containers.
This is much easier to clean up than commerical play dough.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake mix in 2 (8-inch) tins.
Let cool.
Freeze candy in plastic bag for about 30 minutes.
Make the two puddings.
After candy is frozen, break it up inside the bag to bite size pieces, if necessary.

title: meat marinade
directions: Combine marinade ingredients.
Pour small amount (enough to cover bottom) in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Place meat in pan. Top with remaining marinade.
Pierce meat generously with sharp fork.
Turn meat and pierce again.
Cover.
Refrigerate for at least 8 hours or overnight, piercing and turning meat often. Before cooking, let beef come to room temperature.

title: lemon butter sauce(low-cal)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small saucepan and heat until margarine melts.
Pour over cooked, drained vegetables.

title: easy crust
directions: Mix flour, salt, sugar, oil and milk in a large pie plate with fork and shape into crust.

title: fresh apple cake(diabetic recipe)
directions: Combine flour, dates, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves and soda. Cream margarine.
Add egg, vanilla, apple juice and sugar substitute.
Stir in flour mixture, apples, nuts and raisins. Spray 8 x 12-inch pan with Pam.
Add mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cherry mousse
directions: In a bowl, combine gelatin powder and cherries; fold in the whipped topping.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: spicy molasses cookies
directions: In mixing bowl, cream Crisco and brown sugar.
Add egg and molasses; beat until fluffy.
Combine flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Chill well for about 3 hours.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls and dip one side in granulated sugar.
Place square side up on ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool on rack. Makes about 48 cookies.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add shortening with eggs, milk and vanilla.
Make soft dough and either roll in a pan or pat into pan thin.
Put strips or thin pats on top of rhubarb.

title: dill pickles
directions: Put dill in quart jars.
Pack small cucumbers in jars.
Boil brine and let stand a minute and then pour over pickles.
Seal and process.
Good and Hot!

title: marinated tomatoes
directions: Mash the garlic with the salt and blend into the oil and vinegar.
Mix the dressing with the tomatoes, parsley and fresh basil.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Pour half mixture in cooking dish. Spread layer of onion rings and cheese.
Put remaining mixture on top of that, then another layer of onion rings and cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook hamburger meat with onions, then drain.
Add tomatoes (can also use peas) and cook a little.
Put in a Pyrex dish.
Then add squash over it.
Add cheese that has been grated on top.
Add cracker crumbs.
Top with melted butter.
Brown in oven.
What I like is you can fix this the day before.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake according to directions, making two 8-inch layers.
Split both layers horizontally after they have cooled. Blend sugar, sour cream and 1 (6 ounce) coconut.
Chill for 30 minutes.
Spread all but 1 cup of sour cream mixture between the four layers.
Blend remaining cup of sour cream mixture with Cool Whip.
Spread on top and sides of cake.
Add remaining coconut by sprinkling on cake.
Refrigerate.

title: christmas aroma
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil and then slowly simmer on stove, adding more water and apple cider as needed for a delicious Christmas aroma.

title: applesauce spice bar cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease oblong pan.
Cream sugar, eggs and shortening and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and spread into pan.
Bake 25 minutes and ice with Brown Butter Icing.

title: biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Rub in shortening with fingertips or cut in with two knives.
Add liquid and mix to a soft dough. Toss on slightly floured board, pat into shape and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake 15 minutes in hot oven (450°).

title: oatmeal goodies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, oats, pecans and raisins. Add flour, cinnamon, soda and salt.
Mixture is very thick.
Roll into small balls and roll in sugar.
Pat once with fork.
Top with pecan half.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: sue's cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix well and shape into about 30 to 40 meatballs. Bake in oven 350° until all browned, turn once.
Add to cocktail sauce.

title: meat loaf
directions: Bake in loaf pans for 1 hour at 400°.

title: peanut butter swirl bars
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together flour and baking powder and add to batter.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on top.
Place in 350° oven for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and run a knife through to marbleize.
Return to oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: parsley potatoes
directions: In a saucepan, cook potatoes in water, covered, until tender. Drain.
Combine butter and parsley.
Pour over potatoes.
Toss to coat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: layered seafood pizza
directions: Mix cream cheese until smooth.
Add mayonnaise, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice and seasonings.
Spread evenly in a circle onto a round glass or silver serving platter.
Refrigerate while preparing other toppings.
Chop half the shrimp.
Layer ingredients on top of cream cheese as follows: cocktail sauce, chopped shrimp, cheese, green onions, green pepper and olives. Arrange whole shrimp on top.
This should resemble a pizza.
Serve with salted crackers.

title: strawberry slush
directions: Combine ingredients.
Freeze overnight.
Fill glass 3/4 full with slush and add 7-Up.
Enjoy.

title: 20 minute chocolate cake(good cake!)
directions: Put dry flour and sugar in bowl.
Next, bring oleo, oil, water and cocoa to boil in pan.
Add eggs, buttermilk, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Bake 20 minutes at 400° or 28 minutes at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: eagle brand magic cookie bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan in oven.
Spread crumbs over butter and spread condensed milk over them.
Spread rest of ingredients over top.
Press down firmly.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly brown.
Cool and cut in bars.
Makes 24 to 30 bars.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix well and put in airtight glass jar.
Use 1 tablespoon per cup.

title: white trash
directions: Preheat oven to 200°. Mix all ingredients in a very large pan. Bake for 40 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes. After taking out of oven, spread mix on 2 or 3 greased cookie sheets. Let cool and harden. Break into pieces.

title: golden parmesan potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes.
Cut into eighths.
Combine flour, cheese, salt and pepper in a bag.
Moisten potatoes with water and shake a few at a time in bag, coating well.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Place potatoes in a layer in pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour until golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: sausage recipe
directions: Cut meat into small pieces before grinding.
Sprinkle seasoning over meat, mixing well, then grind.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except butter and stuffing.
Put in oven at 325° until cheese melts.
Mix butter and stuffing together and sprinkle over the top.
Brown in oven.

title: my so simple meat loaf
directions: In bowl, combine all ingredients well.
Shape into a loaf. Pour tomato sauce or catsup on top for added touch.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: easy chicken
directions: Put chicken into a baking dish; do not layer.
Pour wine until it is 3/4 up on chicken.
Heavily sprinkle chicken with garlic and pepper.
Add pats of butter to wine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: italian beef pie
directions: Prepare 1 (9-inch) pie crust.
Fry hamburg and onion.
Put 1 layer of Swiss cheese on pie crust.
Add layer hamburg and layer of sauce.
Put another layer of Swiss cheese, hamburg and sauce. Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
(The sauce is made with the Prima Salsa and the beaten eggs.)

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Soak cabbage in hot water and remove leaves.
Mix meat, onion, rice, salt, pepper and sugar together.
Shape into balls and wrap in leaves.
Place in crock-pot and pour tomatoes over.
Cook about 3 to 3 1/2 hours or until done.

title: cherry cake
directions: Mix the dry ingredients (first 4) and set aside.
Mix other ingredients.
Mix all together.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake in 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: awfully good beans
directions: Pick over beans; rinse well.
Cover with water; bring to a boil for 5 minutes.
Allow to stand in the water, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Drain beans and place them in a saucepan with water to cover.
Simmer, partially covered, until the beans are tender, but not mushy, about 45 minutes.
Heat the butter and olive oil in a heavy saucepan.
Add the beans, marjoram or savory, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook 5 to 8 minutes.
The beans should taste awfully good and be soft, but not mushy.

title: raspberry yogurt cake
directions: Cream together butter and brown sugar.
Beat egg and vanilla into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda, then stir into mixture.
Stir in yogurt.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan at 350° for 45 minutes (or less).

title: summer coolness delicious dessert
directions: Mix together flour, margarine and pecans.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Let cool completely. Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Spread over cooled crust.
Mix pudding and milk.
Spread over cream cheese. Top all with more Cool Whip and chopped pecans.
(The second layer can be 8 ounces of cream cheese, 2 tablespoons milk and 1/2 cup powdered sugar, if desired.)

title: sausage casserole
directions: All amounts can be adjusted to family size.

title: easy napoleons
directions: Brush dough with butter and sprinkle with sugar.
Fold and repeat until you have 8 to 10 sheets.
Cut into slices.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.
Let cool.
Brush with jam.
Spread one with cream, top with another slice.

title: rice and mushrooms
directions: Combine ingredients and place in an 8-inch baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for one hour.
Serves 4.

title: one and one casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Crumble ground beef into a buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle with the rice and onion soup mix. Blend the mushroom soup and water together and pour it over the rice. Spread the onion tops over the mixture. Cover and bake for 1 hour.

title: confetti con queso
directions: In a medium saucepan, stir together Taco Bell brand salsa con queso, Taco Bell thick-n-chunky salsa, Taco Bell taco sauce and half the chopped bell peppers.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thoroughly heated.
Transfer to a serving bowl.
Sprinkle with remaining chopped bell peppers.
Serve with Taco Bell tortilla chips.
Makes 3 cups or 8 to 10 servings.
Takes 5 minutes.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Chop vegetables.
Pour 1 cup salt over them and allow to stand 30 minutes.
Rinse well with cold water.
Hang in a cloth bag (an old pillow case works well) outside to drain for 2 to 4 hours. Combine vinegar, sugar and alum.
Bring to a boil.
Add vegetable mix.
Bring to a boil and cook for 10 minutes.
Makes 6 to 7 pints.

title: banana orange frosted
directions: Poke a peppermint candy stick into a whole orange and sip the juice through your sweet straw.

title: cranberry salad(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients. Refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: yum-a-setta
directions: In skillet, brown beef and drain.
Then add onion and brown until onion is just tender.
Remove from heat.
Mix onion, beef and tomato soup and set aside.
Cook noodles until just barely soft and then drain.
Add cream of chicken and celery soup and set aside.
Take 4-quart casserole dish and grease or spray with Pam. In bottom of casserole, place 1/3 of meat mixture, then 1/3 of noodle mixture.
Top with layers of American cheese.
Repeat this step 2 more times.
Bake at 350° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: louisiana seafood gumbo
directions: In a 2-gallon stock pot, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Once oil is hot, add flour and stir constantly with wire whisk until brown roux is achieved.
Do not allow roux to scorch.
Should black specks appear in roux, discard and begin again.
Once roux is golden brown, add onions, celery, bell pepper and garlic.
Saute approximately 3 to 5 minutes or until vegetables are wilted.
Add andouille, blend well into vegetable mixture and saute an additional 2 or 3 minutes.
Add claw crabmeat and stir into roux as this will begin to add seafood flavor to the mixture.
Slowly add hot shellfish stock, one ladle at a time, stirring constantly, until all is incorporated.
Bring to a low boil, reduce to simmer and cook approximately 30 minutes.
Add additional stock, if necessary to retain volume.

Add green onions and parsley and season to taste using salt, pepper and Louisiana gold pepper sauce. Fold shrimp, lump crabmeat, oysters and reserved liquid into soup. Return to a low boil and cook approximately 5 minutes.
Adjust seasonings and serve over cooked rice.
Serves 12.
Preparation time:
1 hour.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients except apples in large bowl.
Add peeled, diced apples to mixture and mix again.
Spread evenly into ungreased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: indiana wood chuck
directions: Cook together as for white sauce; add tomato soup, cheese, mushrooms and pimentos.
Simmer slowly until peppers are tender. Add 4 to 8 hard-boiled eggs.
Serve over chow mein noodles or whatever.
Enjoy.

title: beef and plums
directions: Brown meat in a little oil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add onions and cook until soft.
Heat brandy in small pan.
Ignite and pour over meat.
Shake pan gently until flame dies.
Beat sour cream with the stock, lemon rind and juice.
Stir a little of liquid into flour to make a smooth paste.
Return to liquid mixture and mix well.
Pour over meat.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix 1 cup of hot water with jello.
Add cake mix, eggs (one at a time) and oil.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: barbecued duck
directions: Combine first seven ingredients to make sauce and simmer for about 10 minutes.
Cut duck into halves and barbecue, turning several times and basting generously with sauce until tender. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt; mix and heat until shortening melts.
Add cold water, egg, yeast dissolved in warm water and sugar; sprinkle on top set until dissolved.
When lukewarm, stir in flour to make dough heavy enough to handle. Place in greased bowl; set to rise double in size.
Punch down and make into pan rolls; grease pan with shortening.
Oil top (or place butter on top before baking).
Makes 24 rolls.
Bake at 375° until brown.
Butter tops while still hot.

title: white wine cake
directions: Boil 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir 1/4 cup white wine.
Pour 1/2 glaze over cake as soon as you remove from oven. Cool for 10 minutes.
Remove cake from pan and then pour remaining glaze over cake.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Cut onions into 1/4-inch slices and separate into rings.
Mix next 4 ingredients together until smooth.
Dip each ring into batter.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: millionaire pickles
directions: Dice cucumbers, onions and peppers.
Let stand in salt overnight.
Drain.
Boil syrup 10 minutes, then add cucumbers, onions, green peppers and pimentos.
Boil 20 minutes.
Can and seal.

title: homemade banana pudding
directions: Combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt in double boiler.
Mix in 1 whole egg and 3 egg yolks.
Stir in milk.
Cook, uncovered, over boiling water.
Stir constantly until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Spread small amount on bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with wafers and bananas.
Pour 1/3 custard and alternate to make three layers.

title: duke's crab cakes
directions: Pick the crabmeat to remove shells.
Mix all ingredients with crabmeat.
Be careful not to break up the crabmeat too much. Portion crabcakes by using a ice cream scoop.
Place crabcakes on sheet pan with deli paper.
Place in frying pan or oven.
Cook until done.

title: sliced herbed potatoes
directions: Wash and rinse potatoes. Cut into slices.
Place potatoes in a casserole dish.
Drizzle with melted butter and add herbs. Save cheese to be added 5 minutes before potatoes are done.
Bake at 425° for 50 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: shell beans italiano
directions: After shelling beans, rinse in cold water, then place in saucepan to boil, adding salt pork or bacon.
Let cook hard at first, then turn down, draining water until beans are just covered.
Add tomatoes, then herbs (fresh, if possible).
Stir occasionally with wooden spoon.
Cook gently about an hour, until tender.

title: chicken etouffee
directions: Spray skillet with Pam and brown chicken.
Season chicken with Tony Chachere's Tabasco herbs and spices and Tabasco-seasoned salt*.
Cook vegetables in melted butter until onions are translucent.
Add soup and Ro-Tel to vegetables.
Mix well.
Add vegetable-soup mixture to chicken and simmer approximately 30 minutes.
Serve on rice.

title: mississippi mud
directions: Blend flour, margarine, and pecan chips together.
Spread in a 9 X 13-inch pan.
Bake for 12 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.

title: pork chow mein
directions: Cook pork in 1 tbsp. hot oil till done. Saut celery, onions and mushrooms in 2 tbsp. oil until tender, 2-3 minutes stirring often. Blend cornstarch and 1/4 c. broth. Add rest of broth and soy sauce. Add broth mix and meat to vegetable mixture along with bean sprouts and water chestnuts. Heat and stir until thickened. Serve over rice or chow mein noodles.

title: eggless chocolate cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Combine flour and next 4 ingredients; stir well.
Add flour mixture to water mixture.
Beat at low speed of an electric mixer until well blended.
Beat an additional 1 minute at high speed.
Pour batter into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool completely in pan on a wire rack.
Sprinkle powdered sugar over top of cake.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: tunnel of fudge cake
directions: In a large bowl, cream butter; add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually add sugar, continue creaming at high speed until light and fluffy.
By hand, stir in flour, frosting mix and nuts until well blended.
Pour batter into greased Bundt pan.
Bake in preheated moderate oven (350°) for 60 to 65 minutes.
Since cake has a soft, fudgy interior, test for doneness after 60 minutes by observing dry, shiny brownie-type crust.
When cake is done, cool in pan 2 hours, then remove from pan and cool completely before serving.
This cake is delicious plain or with an old fashioned icing.

title: spicy sweet potatoes
directions: Mash hot sweet potatoes.
Add butter, sugar, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add egg and 1/2 cup graham cracker crumbs.
Continue mashing until completely mixed.
Chill if not firm.
Form mixture into ball using 1/3 cup for each ball and placing 3 miniature marshmallows in center of each.
Dredge balls in graham cracker crumbs.
Place in baking pan and bake in hot oven at 400° for about 10 to 15 minutes.
Yield:
8 sweet potato balls.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well except pepper and cheese.
Pour half the batter into greased, heated 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread the jalapeno peppers and cheese over batter.
Pour remaining batter. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Yields 12 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine in casserole dish.
Put in a layer of stuffing mix.
Mix all ingredients and pour on top of stuffing mix. Sprinkle top with another layer of stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Remove crust from bread and cube.
Fry bacon and crumble.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer bread, cheese and bacon.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Combine yeast, 1 tablespoon sugar and lukewarm water.
Add sugar, shortening and salt to milk; cool.
Add beaten eggs and yeast mixture to milk. Add flour and mix well.
Put dough in greased bowl and brush with melted shortening.
Cover and chill in refrigerator.
Place dough on lightly floured board and roll into 8 inch circle.
Brush with melted shortening.
Cut in shapes of pie pieces.
Let rise until doubled.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple and juice to boil.
Stir in Jell-O until well dissolved.
Cool and add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Fold in nuts. Pour into 3-quart casserole.
This sets up fast.

title: chicken sour cream
directions: Mix cream of mushroom soup with sour cream and pour over chicken.
Add stuffing mixture.
Mix with broth and pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: *chocolate rocky road pie*
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk.
Cook at medium for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Fold in marshmallows and nuts.
Turn into prepared crust.
Chill until firm.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cranberry-orange nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda.
Add orange juice, egg, shortening and orange peel.
Mix well.
Add cranberries and nuts.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook chicken broth, onions, peppers and celery in a 3-quart saucepan for 30 minutes.
Let simmer and add broccoli. Simmer for 15 minutes more.
Add scalded milk.
Simmer for 10 minutes more and thicken with melted butter and flour.
After mixing the 2 ingredients together, let simmer until serving.

title: charlie's drive-in special
directions: On any Monday or Wednesday, drive out to Charlie's.
Order 2 hot dogs (not foot long) with mustard, catsup, light onions and chili.
(Not too many onions if you're visiting afterwards.)
Best eaten with French fries and a cold mug of root beer.
Best to go before noon for pleasant conversation with Charles and Carmen. Even better if topped off with remainder of root beer and add a large scoop of ice cream.
Stir vigorously.
Use only glass mug.

title: cherry cheese cups
directions: Mix together first four ingredients.
Put 1 vanilla wafer in mini cupcake paper.
Fill 3/4 full with mixture.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Top with cherry pie filling.

title: chocolate pecan bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, cocoa and salt.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Stir in 1 beaten egg.
Press mixture evenly on bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: grilled lemon chicken
directions: Squeeze lemon juice into a small bowl.
Add next 5 ingredients and stir.
Put into Ziploc bag and add chicken pieces.
Seal and refrigerate, turning every 15 minutes, until ready to grill. Place aluminum foil on grill and punch small holes in it.
Spray lightly with Pam or a pat of butter.
Grill chicken until tender.

title: my kid's cheesy dog pizza
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed.
Place pizza dough in shallow baking pan.
Spread ketchup on pizza dough.
Place cut up hot dog pieces on top of ketchup.
Spread macaroni and cheese on top of hot dogs.
Bake 11 to 13 minutes or until crust is golden brown at 350°.
Can substitute bologna if desired.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Put hen in a pot.
Add water, salt and pepper.
Let boil for 1 1/2 hours.
Let simmer.
Add mushrooms.
Let simmer.
Make dumplings by mixing flour with chicken broth and baking powder. Mix well.
Roll and cut flour dough and mix with chicken.
Add poultry seasoning and sugar.
Let simmer until dumplings are well done.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown beef and drain fat; add Ragu and mix.
Boil noodles 1/2 time required on package and drain.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer in order:
sauce mixture, noodles, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat until all ingredients are used (usually 2 layers). Make certain top layer of noodles are completely covered with cheeses.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: special peach pie
directions: Drain peaches, reserving 1/2 cup syrup.
Mash peaches and set aside.
In saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over reserved syrup; stir over low heat until gelatin dissolves.
Blend into pudding with 1/2 cup mashed peaches and flavoring.
Beat egg whites until soft peaks form; gently fold into pudding.
Pour into pie shell; chill 4 hours or until firm.
Garnish with remaining peaches.

title: fudge dessert
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar, beat well.
Dissolve cocoa in butter.
Add to sugar and egg mixture.
Add sifted flour and other ingredients.
Pour in unbuttered pan and place in another pan of water.
Bake 45 minutes until crisp on top at 350°.
Cut into squares and serve with ice cream.

title: fried catfish
directions: Heat oil to 365° in frying pan.
Combine corn meal, flour, salt, pepper, garlic, salt and onion salt.
Coat fish.
Place in hot fryer.
Cook 3 minutes on each side.
Garnish with lemons.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Wash and hull berries.
In a saucepan, mix one-half of the berries, cut up, with the sugar and cornstarch.
Cook until really thick.
Cool slightly.
Place remaining berries, whole or cut up, in the bottom of the baked pie shell.
Spread with cooked berries. Cool in the refrigerator.
Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip before serving.

title: crab meat fondue
directions: Combine crab and celery.
Combine mayo, mustard and salt.
Add and mix with crab and celery. Spread between bread slices and cheese slices. Alternate layers of sandwiches and cheese in greased baking dish.
Beat eggs. Add milk and Worcestershire sauce. Pour into baking dish. Cover and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: super good and super quick fudge
directions: Melt margarine and chips in double boiler. Add other ingredients.
Spread in pan.
Very good!

title: tuna potato puffs
directions: Drain and flake tuna; mix with potatoes.
Stir in egg yolks. Add salt, pepper and onion; fold in egg whites.
Pour mixture in greased custard cups or casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese spaghetti casserole
directions: Saute beef in pan.
Pour off grease.
Add tomatoes, sauce, paste and seasonings.
Simmer, stirring often, for at least 1 hour. Cook noodles, and drain.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour and salt and blend well; slowly add milk, stirring constantly. Cook over medium heat until thick.
Add cheeses.
Stir until melted.
Use a 2-quart dish.
Beginning with noodles, meat and cheese; repeat.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add oil, soda, cinnamon, pumpkin and flour.
Mix.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients with the exception of the onion rings. Place in a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Place onions on top near end of cooking.

title: cream cheese dessert
directions: In small mixing bowl, combine pudding mix and milk. Beat on low speed to mix. Add cream cheese, increase speed and beat until smooth and thickened. Pour
into individual or large serving dish. Top with pie filling and refrigerate.

title: eclair cake
directions: Prepare both packages of instant pudding.
Set aside.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Mix dessert topping with pudding.
Pour 1/2 pudding/topping mixture over crackers.
Top with another layer of graham crackers or first frost crackers with chocolate frosting before placing on top.
Fill in cracks for smooth top.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Melt margarine. Add soup and sour cream. Mix well. Add onion, then potatoes and cheese. Empty in casserole dish. Salt and pepper. Cook 1 hour until hash browns are golden brown at 350°.

title: brown sugar carrots
directions: Put butter in small bowl and microwave on High for 45 to 60 seconds.
Add sugar and cinnamon.
Mix with carrots on glass casserole.
Cover and microwave on High for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: banana sticky buns
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brush 10 muffin cups with melted margarine.
Place about 1 teaspoon marmalade, 2 banana slices and about 1 teaspoon coconut in each muffin cup.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits.
Place 1 biscuit in each prepared muffin cup; press down lightly.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until deep golden brown.
Immediately invert and remove from pan.
Makes 10 rolls.

title: cranberry torte
directions: Mix cranberries and sugar;
set aside for about 1 hour. Cover bottom of ungreased 8-inch square pan with wafer crumbs. Cream butter and	sugar.	Add
eggs,
one
at a time, and beat until light and fluffy.
Spread over crumbs.
Top with drained cranberries and
then
nuts.
Top
with
cream.
Sprinkle with additional	crumbs	or
nuts.
Refrigerate	several
hours	or overnight.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook bacon until crisp. Pour off fat and add water. Cook potatoes and stir in chicken soup. Add milk, salt, pepper, and onions. Mix all together and cook on low heat until hot.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Place croutons in greased 13-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese and crumbled, cooked sausage.
In a separate bowl, beat the eggs and add the rest of the ingredients.
Pour this mixture into the baking dish.
It will be very full.
Bake at 300° for 90 minutes.

title: english pea salad
directions: Add salad dressing to ingredients to taste.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake in a loaf pan at 375° for 1 hour.
This flour has everything in it and the beer has the yeast.

title: crock-pot chocolate
directions: Put all ingredients in crock-pot.
Do not stir!
Put crock-pot on high for 30 minutes.
Turn on medium for 1 hour.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper.
Let set overnight.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: texas hash
directions: Boil rice, then drain.
Brown ground beef, then drain grease off.
Add taco seasoning mix.
When hamburger is ready, add it to the rice.
Then add tomatoes and also some water to make juice. Cook long enough to get mixed together real good.

title: chili with beans
directions: Quick soak beans in 5-quart pan.
Bring water to boil; add beans, then boil for 5 to 7 minutes.
Allow beans to soak for 1 hour; wash.
Then crumble ground beef (uncooked) into crock-pot. Add all other ingredients; stir slowly.
Set crock-pot on medium-high.
Cook for 3 to 4 hours.
Chili is done when beans are tender; the longer it cooks, the better it tastes.
Serve with grated Cheddar cheese, extra chopped onions and cornbread.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream margarine and oil.
Add sugar and beat until smooth. Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda together and add to egg yolk mixture.
Add buttermilk, vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour batter in three 8-inch pans.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350° until done.
Add Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: chicken breasts with adobado sauce
directions: Remove the seeds from the chilies and lightly roast to develop the full flavor.
Soak in the vinegar (add enough water to cover) for 15 minutes, then puree.
Brown the onions, then add the garlic puree and cumin.
Add the chili puree and stock.
Let cook for about 20 minutes or until the flavors have all merged.

title: bubba's cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in 2 (13 x 9-inch) pans at 375° until done.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill before serving.

title: lemonade chicken
directions: Combine flour with 1 1/4 teaspoons salt.
Coat chicken thoroughly.
Brown chicken pieces on all sides in hot oil; drain. Transfer to crock-pot.
Stir together thawed lemonade concentrate, brown sugar, catsup and vinegar.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and cook on high heat for 3 to 4 hours or on low for 6 to 8 hours. Remove chicken; pour cooking liquid into saucepan.
Return chicken to cooker; cover to keep warm.
Skim fat from reserved liquid.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: mashed potato casserole(makes 12 to 15 servings)
directions: Boil potatoes until soft.
With mixer, beat cream cheese and sour cream.
Add potatoes gradually.
Beat until smooth.
Beat in garlic salt and pepper.
Turn mixture into a buttered shallow 3 or 4-quart casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Cover with lid or foil.

title: world's best cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream together butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Add egg, mixing well, then oil, mixing well. Add oats, Rice Krispies, coconut and nuts, stirring well.
Then add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well and form into balls about the size of a walnut and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Flatten with fingertips and bake for 12 to 15 minutes.
Allow to cool for a few minutes before removing.

title: punch bowl pudding(english trifle)
directions: *Coated with either juice from 2 fresh oranges or 3 tablespoons lemon juice (prevents darkening).

title: hoosier persimmon roll
directions: Thaw persimmons.
Combine ingredients in order given and mix together.
Spoon about 1/3 of mixture on a sheet of wax paper, shape in a roll.
Wrap in moisture proof material and freeze. Repeat until all mixture is used.
To serve, cut the slightly thawed roll in slices for individual servings.
Top with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.
Makes about 24 servings.

title: chicken crescent rolls
directions: Mix ingredients and scoop onto crescent rolls.
Pinch corners around the meat and seal.
May be made ahead and refrigerated until mealtime.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter; add cake mix and eggs.
Stir well.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate crispy treats
directions: Line 11 x 7-inch baking pan with foil, letting ends come over sides.
Lightly grease the foil.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until tender; drain and cool.
Add onion and pepper.
Mix other ingredients and pour over carrots.
Let set for 12 hours.
Keeps well in the refrigerator as long as 2 weeks.

title: pineapple icebox cake
directions: Put vanilla wafers on bottom of bowl.
Cream butter and sugar; beat eggs separately (beat whites and yolks separately) and fold in.
Add pineapple.
Fold in whipped cream.
Cover with vanilla wafers.

title: egg casserole
directions: Layer rolls in greased 9 x 13-inch dish.
Place sausage on rolls.
Sprinkle
cheese
over
sausage.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over
cheese.	Bake
at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients together.
Sift last 3 ingredients with flour.
Also sift baking soda with flour.
Pour into greased and floured rectangle pan.
This recipe very good plain or with a plain white icing.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine beef, 3 tablespoons steak sauce, egg, bread crumbs and salt.
Make 24 balls.
Brown meatballs in oil.
Drain.
Add rest of ingredients except green pepper and cornstarch.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in 1 tablespoon water. Stir into mixture.
Add green pepper.
Simmer, uncovered, 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat together butter, sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture and milk alternately to butter mixture.
Spread batter on a cookie sheet with raised edges or a jelly roll pan.
Place apples on batter in rows.
Melt 1/2 stick of butter and pour over apples.
Mix 1/2 cup sugar with cinnamon and sprinkle on apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: valentine vitamin salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and cool.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Mold and chill.
Serve on lettuce with mayonnaise.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Whip until soft and fluffy.
Beat in sugar and peanut butter.
Fold in Cool Whip. Fill graham cracker crust.
Chill until firm, usually several hours.

title: chocolate dipped or drizzled fruit
directions: Rinse fruit in cold water.
Pat dry.

Melt morsels and shortening over hot (not boiling) water, stirring until mixture is smooth. Remove from heat. Cool slightly. Dip fruit about halfway into chocolate mixture. Shake off excess or drizzle chocolate from pastry bag filled with small tip, heavy-duty plastic bag with tiny corner snipped off or plastic squeeze bottle with small tip. Place on wax paper lined tray.
Chill for 15 minutes or until coating is set.

title: potato pancakes
directions: In a bowl, mix potatoes, eggs, flour, cream, salt and onions. In skillet, melt butter.
Drop potato mixture by heaping tablespoons into skillet and fry until golden brown on both sides. Add butter to skillet as needed.

title: caramel glazed pear bars
directions: Drain pears, reserving the syrup.
Finely dice pears.
Cream margarine with sugar.
Blend in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Add to creamed mixture immediately with 1/2 cup reserved pear juice.
Stir in pears, raisins and nuts.
Turn into greased 15 5/8 x 10-inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean when stuck into center of cake.
Spread with caramel glaze while warm.
Cut bars.
Makes 40 bars.

title: mexican corn bake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into an 8 x 10-inch pan or large casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: quick pizza
directions: Brown meat in large frying pan.
Add onion; cook on medium heat until onion is transparent.
Add seasonings.
Cook for approximately 5 minutes.
Roll dough into 12-inch round or square pizza pan.
Place meat mixture on dough.
Add tomato sauce; spread over mixture.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake for 20 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Crust should be a golden brown.
Yields 6 servings.

title: stir-fry chicken and vegetables
directions: Dice chicken and heat oil in a large nonstick frypan or wok. Stir-fry chicken.
Add onion; stir until done.
Cook vegetables according to package directions.
Add to chicken.
Add 2 to 3 tablespoons soy sauce.
Add stir-fry sauce to taste.
Stir to mix well.
This is good alone with toast or eaten over rice.

title: chinese pepper steak
directions: Cut meat in half lengthwise with a sharp knife, then crosswise into thin slices.
Cook meat, onion and pepper in skillet in hot oil until meat is browned.
Stir in remaining ingredients except rice.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Serve over rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: mona newbern's dill pickles
directions: Wash and scald jars.
Fill half full with cucumbers.
Add 1 teaspoon of dill seed, 1 pod of pepper and 1 clove garlic; finish filling jars with cucumbers.
Pour brine (water, vinegar and salt) over cucumbers; seal.
Let cure for 3 weeks.

title: shrimp my way
directions: Peel and devein shrimp. Melt butter in heavy skillet. Saute onions and celery until tender. Add tomatoes, shrimp and seasonings. Simmer for 30 minutes. Serve over hot rice.

title: mexicorn dip
directions: Mix all together and serve with corn chips.

title: no bake cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add sour cream and vanilla; fold in whipped topping and blend well.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set at least 4 hours.
Garnish with fresh strawberries.

title: potatoes au gratin
directions: Combine all ingredients, except crumbs.
Mix lightly.
Pour into 1-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tuna-apple salad
directions: Drain tuna. Break into large pieces.
Combine all ingredients except lettuce. Chill thoroughly.
Serve on lettuce.

title: texas chili
directions: Brown meat in small amount of cooking oil.
Add onion.
When meat is brown, cover with water and simmer covered for 30 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and thicken with 1 tablespoon flour dissolved in 1/2 cup water. Continue cooking until thickened.
Add cooked beans, if desired.

title: pumpkin pie(kelley jo's great, great, great grandmother eldridge)
directions: Mix as given.
Pour into pastry-lined pan.
Bake about 10 minutes at 375°.
Reduce heat to 350° and finish baking.
A knife inserted halfway between crust and center will come out clean when pie is done.
Top with fresh whipped cream.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Crust:
Combine with a fork, crumbs, sugar and melted butter until wet.

title: hot dog bean casserole
directions: Stir together all of the ingredients in a 2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Serve hot.
Yield:
5 (3/4 cup) servings.

title: blueberry squares
directions: Sift in a bowl the flour and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Take out 3/4 cup of mixture and set aside.
Add baking powder, salt, egg yolks and milk.
Beat until well blended.
In a separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Scatter blueberries on top of batter.
Sprinkle
the set aside dry mixture over the top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: gooey bars
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients with beater.
Press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the next 3 ingredients with beater; pour on top of first mixture in pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle remainder of powdered sugar (2 tablespoons) on top after removing from oven.

title: peas and asparagus casserole
directions: Mix milk, soup and cheese.
Add peas, asparagus and water chestnuts.
Bake about 45 minutes at 325°.
Dot butter on top 10 minutes before done.
Add potato chips on top.

title: eggplant rollatini
directions: In a small bowl, place 1 tablespoon of the oil.
Using a pastry brush, brush 1 side of each eggplant slice with the oil.
Heat a 12-inch nonstick skillet over moderately high heat.
Place a layer of the eggplant slices in the skillet, oiled sides down and cook, covered, for 6 minutes, turning once.
Transfer the eggplant to a plate and let cool.
Repeat with the remaining slices.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Break up sausage and brown in skillet.
Drain grease when no longer pink.
Mix Bisquick, cheese and sausage with a fork.
Beat together remaining ingredients and add to sausage and Bisquick. Blend well with your hands.
Shape into balls.
Place on baking sheet and flatten slightly.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Good party hors d'oeuvre or breakfast item.

title: apple cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg and add 1/2 of dry ingredients.
Blend in the milk and add rest of dry ingredients. Add nuts, raisins and apples.
Drop on greased cookie sheets. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Ice with confectioners sugar, milk and Crisco mixed to form icing.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and sit aside to cool.

title: baugh's barbecue sauce
directions: Cook pork roast until tender.
Slice thinly.
Mix remaining ingredients.
More brown sugar may be added, if desired.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Sauce is very thin.
Add sauce to meat and heat. Serve on rye bread with pickle and onion.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Heat pumpkin in saucepan over moderate heat for 10 minutes until somewhat dry, stirring frequently.
Stir in butter.
Mix together sugars, salt and spices; mix with hot pumpkin.
Beat eggs slightly; add evaporated milk and water and gradually stir into pumpkin mixture.
Pour into a 9-inch shell.
Bake at 475° for 10 minutes and at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cole slaw
directions: Night before, mix dressing.
Add to shredded cabbage, green pepper and carrots.
Refrigerate.

title: white chicken chili
directions: Saute onion. Add chicken. Cook for 2 minutes. Add broth, beans, corn and salsa. Cook 10 to 15 minutes. Top with sour cream, cheese and cilantro (optional).

title: crock-pot dressing
directions: Bake cornbread following directions on box.
Cool and crumble. Toast light bread and cube.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into crock-pot.
Cook on low temperature for 3 hours or cook on high temperature for 2 hours.

title: mincemeat pecan buns
directions: Mix and sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Work in shortening with pastry cutter.
Add milk; mix thoroughly and pat out on floured board to 1/4-inch thickness.
Brush with melted butter and spread with mincemeat.
Roll as a jelly roll.
Cut in 1-inch slices and place on a baking sheet which has been heavily coated with butter.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and pecan halves. Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Remove from pan and serve, pecan side up.

title: chocolate marshmallow squares
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven. Break marshmallows in half and cover over the hot batter.
Return to oven (which has been turned off) for 2 or 3 minutes or until marshmallows begin to spread.
Cool.
Ice with your favorite chocolate frosting.
I bake these bars one day and then cut them the next day.
They cut better then.
Also freeze well.

title: apple pie filling
directions: Quarter or cube enough firm apples for 7 quarts.
Pack loosely in jars.
Mix ingredients and pour over apples.
Seal and boil in water bath for 20 minutes.
When needed, pour in prepared pie shells and bake.

title: parisienne potatoes
directions: Using a melon baller, scoop out 6 balls from each potato. Place potato balls in a saucepan with water to cover.
Cook until tender; drain well.
Saute potato balls in butter until golden brown.
Toss with parsley.
For 8 people.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Melt butter in pan or bowl in microwave.
Add cinnamon.
Stir in well.
Dip marshmallows in butter and cinnamon.
Put biscuits in cupcake pan, flat and thin.
Add one marshmallow to each biscuit, then wrap biscuit over marshmallow.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Makes 10 cinnamon rolls.

title: pinto beans caliente
directions: Wash beans.
Place dry salt bacon in crock-pot and add washed beans.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons garlic salt.
Cover with water to 1 inch above beans.
Let stand overnight or until water is absorbed.
After soaking, add water until 1 inch of water covers beans.
Add 1 tablespoon garlic salt, pepper and chili powder; stir.
Cook on high setting of crock-pot for 1 hour.
Add more water to keep beans covered.
Cook an additional 5 hours on low setting.
Try soaking beans in beer (less gas).

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve with boiled shrimp.

title: mexican chili dip
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Put all ingredients in large pot and cook slowly for at least 45 minutes.
Serve as a dip, as a meal or on hot dogs.

title: venison summer sausage or very lean beef
directions: Note:
Makes 3 rolls of sausage (1 pound each).

title: pumpkin pie(2 pies)
directions: Put eggs in a large bowl.
Add pumpkin.
Combine white sugar, brown sugar, pumpkin pie spice and salt in a small bowl.
Stir these ingredients into pumpkin and eggs.
Gradually stir in 3 cups evaporated milk.
Pour into 2 unbaked 9-inch pie shells.
