title: egg and sausage quiche
directions: Press hash browns into 13 x 9 inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes in 350 degree oven.
Fry sausage.
Spread on top of hash browns.
Spread cheese on top.
Mix together eggs, milk, mushrooms and onions, and pour on top.
Put back in oven and bake at 350 degrees until eggs are set.

title: ham and cheese bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
Unroll crescent roll dough on an ungreased baking sheet.
Pinch perforated edges together to make 1 solid sheet of dough.

title: wade's shrimp spread
directions: Finely chop the shrimp. Stir in the rest of the ingredients; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight. Serve with crackers.

title: oriental rice
directions: Lightly brown 1 1/2 cups uncooked brown rice in dry skillet. Add 4 cups water; cover and simmer until done.
Do not stir.
Use 4 cups of rice.
Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Mix together ground meat,
rice, salt, pepper, 1 tablespoon butter and 1 cup
lemon
juice.
Mix well.
Boil cabbage in pot until soft.
When cabbage
is ready, take one leaf with rice mixture; roll up and put
in
bottom
of
pot.
Place one roll on top of another.
Put 1 to 2 cups of water in bottom of pot and rest of lemon juice
and dab rest of butter on cabbage rolls. Cook until top cabbage rolls are soft.

title: crab dip
directions: Thaw sticks and squeeze out juice.
Put in food processor; cut in chunks.
Mix all ingredients together.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix everything together.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° in bread pans.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and let stand overnight in refrigerator before serving.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Mix sugar, cream of tartar, salt, egg whites and 1/4 cup water in a pot or bowl over simmering water.
Beat steadily over low heat with mixer until the frosting stands in peaks, about 5 to 7 minutes (no more).
Remove from the heat and continue to beat until thick enough to spread.
Add the vanilla before spreading. Makes about 2 cups; enough to fill and frost an 8 or 9-inch (2-layer) cake.

title: hamburger relish
directions: Place all ingredients in a medium size glass bowl; mix well. Cover and let stand at room temperature at least 30 minutes before serving.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: ambrosia(german christmas cookies)
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream butter until fluffy.
Add sugars gradually.
Add eggs, rinds and vanilla.
Mix well.
Add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well by hand.
Drop by teaspoon (or form into small balls and flatten).
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Better if stored awhile to blend flavors.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Mix together and pour 3/4 batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Put the pie filling on top of batter, then dot remaining batter on top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; crumble.
Combine bacon drippings with next 5 ingredients and stir over medium heat until thickened.
Add potatoes, onion and bacon; toss.
Serve warm or cold.
Keeps for a week refrigerated and gets better with time.
Serves 6 easily.

title: copper pennies
directions: Stir into vegetables.
Best if left overnight, 12 hours, before serving.
Can be used as a cold vegetable dish or a side dish.

title: christmas egg casserole
directions: Saute the sausage, drain all the grease and set aside. Beat the eggs, add milk, salt and mustard, stir. Layer the bread cubes on the bottom of a 9 x 13 inch baking dish. Then layer the sausage, followed by cheese. Pour the egg mixture over the top, cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: molasses butterball cookies
directions: Mix butter with molasses until fluffy.
Add flour, beat until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Roll in powdered sugar to coat.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: garfield's lasagna
directions: Wash hands!
Brown beef, drain grease.
This is done with adult help.
Mix spaghetti sauce into ground beef.
Beat eggs.
Add cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese and 1 cup shredded cheese to eggs. Add oregano or Italian seasoning.
Mix well.
Place 3 uncooked lasagna noodles in a 12 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Measure 1 1/3 cups meat mixture and spread over noodles.
Spread 1/2 of egg-cheese mixture over meat mixture.
Repeat noodles, meat, then egg-cheese mixture.
Top with 3 more uncooked noodles and remaining meat mixture.
Pour the hot water around all 4 edges of dish. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Sprinkle remaining Mozzarella cheese on top and cool 10 minutes before serving.

title: jambalaya
directions: Cook ham, onion, celery, green pepper and garlic in oil in large skillet until onion is soft.
Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil; cover.
Simmer 40 minutes, stirring once or twice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: strawberry skillet cookies
directions: In skillet, combine dates, coconut, sugar, butter, egg and salt.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture bubbles and thickens, 5 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in Rice Krispies, chopped pecans and vanilla.
Cool 10 minutes.
For each cookie, use 1 tablespoon of mixture.
Form into strawberry shapes. Keep fingers moist; roll in red sugar.
Trim with artificial leaf you buy at craft shops to form stem of strawberry cookies.
A Christmas goody!

title: mud pie
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease a round pan (8 x 1 1/2-inch) or a pie plate.
Mix granulated sugar, margarine, vanilla, salt, eggs, flour and cocoa in a medium bowl with a wooden spoon; stir in nuts.
Pour into pan.
Bake until wooden pick inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean, about 25 minutes. Immediately prick holes in pie with a wooden pick; spread fudge sauce over top.
Cool completely.

title: cream of coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions.
Use a 13 x 9 inch baking pan.
Remove cake from oven; while hot, prick holes in cake with fork.
Pour mixture of Eagle Brand Milk and cream of coconut over hot cake.
Let mixture soak in.
When cake is cool, frost with cool whip and sprinkle with coconut.

title: green beans
directions: Fry bacon and drain, then add the onion and bell pepper to the bacon drippings and cook until tender.
Add the flour, brown sugar, sauce, salt, pepper, mustard and tomatoes to the onion and peppers and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add the green beans and top with the crumbled bacon.
Heat.

title: minted chocolate mousse
directions: The secret to this dessert is lots of beating!!!

title: grilled mustard and rosemary chicken thighs
directions: Measure mustard into a small bowl.
Whisk in lemon juice, then oil.
Add garlic, rosemary and pepper.
Pour into large non-aluminum pan.
Remove skin from chicken, if desired.
Add chicken to pan and turn to coat.
Cover and marinate 2 hours at room temperature or overnight in the refrigerator.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion. Add soup plus 1/2 can water. Set aside. Spray bottom of cake pan with Pam. Cover bottom with frozen tater tots. Bake at 400 degrees for 10 minutes. Pour meat mixture over tater tots. Cover with grated cheese. Return to oven, bake for 20 minutes at 350 degrees until cheese begins to brown. And to make a complete dinner, serve with a can of mixed vegetables.

title: candy coated carrots
directions: In a saucepan, cook carrots in a small amount of water until crisp-tender. Drain and keep warm. In the same saucepan, cook butter and brown sugar until bubbly. Stir in lemon juice, hot pepper sauce and salt. Return carrots to pan and heat through. Makes 6 servings.

title: different potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients into a dressing mixture.
Begin with a layer of sliced potatoes in a casserole dish.
Spread with dressing mixture.
Continue alternating potatoes and mixture, ending with mixture.
Refrigerate; keeps well.

title: cranberry cookies
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Combine cranberries, dates and nuts.
Beat eggs and lemon flavoring.
Gradually add sugar until all is fluffy.
Add nuts and fruit to beaten sugar mixture. Fold in dry ingredients.
Line 2 1/2 inch paper liners into a muffin pan.
Press mixture into pan liners.
Bake at 300 degrees 45 minutes.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes and store in refrigerator or freezer.

title: yogurt popsicles
directions: Combine strawberries, yogurt and honey in medium size bowl. Put into 6-ounce cup and freeze for 20 minutes.
Add sticks and freeze until firm.
Peel off paper cup before eating.

title: baked eggs
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Make sure both sides of the bread are buttered.
Bake at 350° until firm in middle.

title: asparagus au gratin
directions: Make a sauce by blending 3 tablespoons melted butter, flour, salt and pepper; add liquid and cook over low flame, stirring occasionally, until thick and smooth. Remove from fire; add olives and eggs. Toss bread crumbs and 1 tablespoon melted butter together. Arrange asparagus, buttered crumbs and white sauce mixture in layers in buttered baking dish, having top layer of the crumbs. Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients. Spoon into pie shell and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: 3 minute delight poppy cake
directions: Beat well on medium speed for 3 minutes. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour in a 10 inch angle food tube pan. Do not grease pan. Cool before removing from pan.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix all together and leave set for several hours or overnight.

title: cream filled cupcakes
directions: Mix up cake mix. Fill paper cups 2/3 full; cream the cheese with the sugar.
Beat in egg and salt.
Stir in chocolate; drop in 1 rounded teaspoonful cheese mix on each cupcake.
Bake as package directs (25 to 30 minutes).
Makes about 30.

title: mom's southern pecan pie
directions: Put eggs in a blender; blend until eggs are fluffy and light in color.
Add sugar, syrup and butter, one at a time with blender at low speed.
Turn off blender and add pecans and fill unbaked pie shell.
Put foil around the edge of the pie shell.
Don't cover the filling.
Bake for 10 minutes at 400°; reduce oven to 350° and bake for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage and drain off excess fat.

Separate rolls into rectangles and gently place into bottom and up sides of 9 x 13 inch baking pan. Spoon sausage into crust; sprinkle potatoes and cheddar cheese over sausage. Beat eggs; add milk and seasonings and pour over sausage mixture. Sprinkle with parmesan cheese and bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: peanut butter pie (low-fat and sugar)
directions: Whisk together milk and sour cream. Add pudding and mix well. Add the peanut butter, mixing until blended. Pour into crust. Chill at least 4 hours. Serves 6.

title: tomato salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together with safflower oil.
Serve over onions and sliced tomatoes.

title: chili
directions: Crumble beef into a 2 1/2 to 3-quart casserole.
Cook on High until cooked through.
Add remaining ingredients; stir.
Cover and microwave on High (until temperature reaches 190°) approximately 40 to 45 minutes.
Stir chili and rotate dish halfway through cooking.
After cooking, let stand 10 minutes to blend flavors.

title: microwave penuche
directions: Spread nuts in pie plate.
Microwave uncovered on High 6 to 7 minutes.
Melt butter in a 2 1/2 to 3-quart bowl.
Stir in sugar and milk until blended.
Microwave uncovered on High 12 minutes, stirring 4 times until mixture has thickened and is a caramel color.
Remove bowl; add vanilla.
Beat with mixer 3 to 4 minutes until smooth and shiny.
Add walnuts and beat on low speed 1 minute.
Spread in greased 8-inch pan.
Cool, then cover and refrigerate until firm, 2 to 3 hours.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a tray of self-rising flour.
Work in flour to make a soft dough.
Place in refrigerator and let stand overnight.
Roll out small balls the size of marbles.
Then mash and bake at 325° until light brown.
Remove from pan while still warm to cool.
Store in airtight container.

title: easy salsa snacks
directions: Spread each cracker with cream cheese. Top each with salsa and optional olive slices if desired. Serve immediately.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Soften yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Combine hot water, sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool until lukewarm; stir in whole wheat flour and white flour to make a moderately stiff dough.
Knead until smooth, 10 to 12 minutes.
Let raise; punch down.
Rise again.
Shape into 3 loaves.
Bake for 35 minutes in 375° oven. Cover with foil, if necessary the last 20 minutes.
After baking, grease top with butter.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: one pot stew
directions: In large Dutch oven or ovenproof dish, combine first 8 ingredients; blend well.
Add remaining ingredients and stir to coat.
Bake, covered, at 350°
for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Serves 6.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Yield: 2 1/3 cups mix.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Heat mixture, then add eggs last.
Prepare favorite pie crust and pour in filling.
Bake for 15 minutes at 425°, or until crust is brown.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake for an additional 30 minutes.
Pie is done when knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool.
Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: chicken tepic
directions: Cook the zucchini squash and slice.
Cook, peel, slice and fry the potatoes.
Cook the chicken with 1/2 onion, salt and pepper. Remove and fry the chicken.
Place the chicken in a serving dish. Place the fried potatoes around the plate.
Put the lettuce and zucchini on top.
Liquefy the tomatoes with the rest of the onion; strain and spread over the chicken.
Spread the oregano, chili powder, salt and pepper over the chicken.
Dash some oil and vinegar.
Serve cold.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix together boiling water and oatmeal and let stand for 20 minutes.
Cream together butter and sugars.
Mix oatmeal in, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: working mom's cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In a 13 x 9 cake pan, pour the can of pineapple with the juice in the pan.
Stir in the cherry pie filling.
Pour cake mix over fruit and spread it out evenly.
Do not stir.
Cut the stick of margarine into chunks and distribute over the powder.
Place pecans over the top.
Cook for 1 hour. Allow to cool before serving.

title: sliced beef in sour cream sauce
directions: Saute onions and garlic in butter.
Add beef.
Turn and add seasonings.
Put all vegetables in blender with water to liquify. Pour over roast in roasting pan.
Cook slowly on top of stove or in 350° oven 2 to 2 1/2 hours.
Remove meat from sauce.
Slice. Mix 2 tablespoons flour in sour cream.
Slowly add to sauce, stirring constantly.
Add sliced beef to sauce.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Add sugar, salt and water to tomato puree.
Place bread squares in casserole.
Pour melted butter over bread squares.
Add hot tomato mixture.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.
Excellent served with meat or fish.
Serves 6.

title: chess pie
directions: Warm over low heat.
Then put in pie shell.
Bake at 300° to 350° for 45 minutes.

title: banana parfait punch
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil and simmer for 10 minutes. Cool and then mix in bananas.
Mix the remaining ingredients all together and freeze.
(It's better to freeze this mixture in a large cake taker, so when thawed and other ingredients are added, container will hold one recipe for transport.)
Thaw for 1 hour before serving.
Mix in 3 (2 liter) bottles of ginger ale.
Serves 60.

title: punch
directions: Mix sugar and hot water.
Set aside.
Mix jello as box indicates.
Set aside.
Mix water, pineapple juice, lemonade, almond flavoring.
Stir all ingredients together in a large bowl. Freeze in gallon containers.
Serve slushy and add several scoops of pineapple sherbet to each punch bowl.

title: orange and peach salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Add sugar. Let set until syrupy.
Fold in peaches and extract.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: mexican coffee
directions: Place coffee and cinnamon in filter basket. Add water to coffeemaker and brew. In saucepan, blend milk, chocolate syrup and sugar. Stir until dissolves. Combine milk mixture and brewed coffee. Stir in vanilla and garnish with whipped cream.

title: rice souffle
directions: Melt butter and cheese in milk.
Add rice and salt.
Beat eggs slightly and add to mixture.
Mix thoroughly and pour into greased casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: golden pesto
directions: Place oil, tomatoes, basil, nuts and cheese into a food processor.
Process until smooth.
With machine running add hot water, blending well.
Can be spooned over hot pasta or spread on French bread.
Do not heat the pesto.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, coconut, then flour sifted with soda, salt and baking powder.
Last, add Wheaties. Roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Put on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: granny's cornbread dressing
directions: Mix cornmeal, flour, baking powder, egg and milk in large mixing bowl.
Pour into well-oiled 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in a 450° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Cool and crumble. Cook celery and onion in small amount of water until tender, not mushy.
Drain.
Add Cup-a-Soup mix, chicken broth, bouillon and margarine to crumbled cornbread.
Mix well.
Add the onion, celery and chopped eggs to mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 400° for about 45 minutes or until done.

title: veal meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When done, add 1 can heated mushrooms with liquid on top.

title: canadian cheese soup
directions: Melt butter in large pan.
Add onion, celery and carrots. Saute over low heat until soft.
Add flour and cornstarch and cook until bubbly.
Add stock and milk and stir until smooth.
Add soda and cheese.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add
parsley a few minutes before you serve.
Good with broccoli or cauliflower added.

title: chocolate sparkles
directions: Beat butter and 1 1/4 cups sugar until creamy.
Beat in eggs; add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Mix flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Stir into chocolate mixture; blend well.
Chill dough. Shape dough into balls.
Roll balls in 1/4 cup sugar and place about 2 inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from baking sheet while warm.
Yields 5 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend shortening, sugar, peanut butter, salt and egg.
Add combined dry ingredients and mix well.
Shape into 1 inch balls. Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet and press a crisscross on each ball with a fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: tomato cream pasta sauce
directions: Cook ingredients for 12 minutes, stir in cream at last and simmer 10 more minutes.
Serve over vermicelli.

title: oven chicken stew
directions: Preheat
oven
to
Place
frozen
vegetables
in greased 2 1/2 quart
casserole
or baking dish.
Sprinkle with seasoning salt.
Arrange chicken
on top of the vegetables and sprinkle with seasoning
salt
and
paprika.
Combine the soup and wine; pour over
the chicken and vegetables.
Sprinkle the cheese, parsley flakes and
pimiento over top.
Cover and bake for 1 1/2 hours at
Remove cover and bake an additional 15 minutes.

title: floating cobbler
directions: Mix first
ingredients.
Add
enough
milk to make a thin consistency (consistency similar to cake mixed and ready to bake, may
be slightly thinner).	Pour in bottom of baking pan (approximately
10 x 10-inch).
Pour canned or fresh fruit on top. Dot
with	butter on top (about 2 tablespoons).
Bake at 350° until done.

title: garden tuna salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Stir in remaining.
Chill and serve.

title: zucchini or yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions in boiling water with a pinch of salt added for about 5 minutes, squash MUST still be a little crisp. Drain.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrots, squash and onions.
Add salt to taste.
Combine stuffing mix with melted margarine,
Spread half the stuffing mixture in bottom of a 12 x 7 x 2 in baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture on top of stuffing, then sprinkle the rest of stuffing on top of the vegetable mixture.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: babe's apple cake
directions: Stir together flour, wheat germ, soda, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg; set aside.

title: bar cheese
directions: Cube cheese.
Combine all ingredients in a microwavable bowl. Heat on full power for 6 to 7 minutes, stirring halfway through. Will fill 4 small margarine tubs.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar first in a bowl, then the cream cheese. Add the rest of the ingredients until smooth.
Put in spring-form pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs well with electric mixer or blender; add sugar, a little milk and vanilla.
Mix well and pour into freezer can.
Add enough milk to fill freezer can to fill line.
If you use Eagle Brand milk, do not use eggs.
Freeze until freezer stops or firm.

title: microwave hot fudge sauce
directions: In 1-quart microwave bowl or glass measuring cup, combine sugar, chocolate, butter, evaporated milk and corn syrup. Microwave on High 2 to 3 minutes, stirring after each minute. Cook 3 minutes more, stirring once.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into glass jar.
Cool; cover and store in refrigerator.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Boil broccoli for 5 minutes; drain.
Beat eggs; stir in mayo, mushroom soup, onions and cheese.
Fold in broccoli.
Place entire mixture in casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, in 375° oven for 40 minutes.

title: sweet-sour meat balls
directions: Cut bread in cubes.
Soak in a little cold water until soft. Squeeze out water.
Combine with remaining ingredients except Sweet-Sour Sauce.
Shape in balls the size of walnuts.
Place in jelly roll pan (or brown in skillet containing a little hot fat.) Bake in a very hot oven (450°) for 15 to 18 minutes.
Place balls in Sweet-Sour Sauce and simmer 10 minutes.
If balls are made ahead, add sauce to them and heat in the oven.
Makes about 36 meat balls, 8 to 9 servings.

title: carrot bars
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil, flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix well and add the three jars of baby carrot food.
Pour into greased 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Cool.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown beef, onion, garlic and oregano.
Add soup, water, vinegar and salt.
Simmer 30 minutes.
In a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish, arrange 3 alternate layers of noodles, cottage cheese, meat sauce and Mozzarella.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: chokolade kage(chocolate cake)
directions: Melt the chocolate. Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs and cooled chocolate.
Add milk and dry ingredients.
Add vanilla. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken from around the world(each variation serves 4)
directions: Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add chicken breasts and saute on one side for about 8 minutes.
Turn over and saute other side for 5 minutes longer, until meat is white throughout.
Remove chicken to a plate.
Add the minced garlic to the skillet and stir-fry a few seconds.
Add the wine and oregano and cook until the wine has evaporated for about 10 seconds.
Add tomato sauce and simmer until thickened.
Add parsley and season with the pepper.
Return the chicken to the skillet; coat with the sauce and heat through.
Serve with your favorite pasta.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Layer lettuce, cauliflower, onion and bacon bits.
Mix sour cream, Hellmann's mayonnaise and sugar.
Spread over top.
Seal real good.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Mix well before serving.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine; sprinkle crumbs over butter.
Pour milk and top evenly with chips, coconut and nuts.
Press down and bake 25 to 30 minutes until lightly brown.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Mix peanut butter, garlic, Worcestershire and oil.
Pour this over the mixture of cereals, pretzels and nuts.
Mix well; bake at 225° for 2 hours; stir every 30 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in a cast-iron skillet, if possible, at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: easy breakfast roll
directions: Cut frozen bread dough into 12 equal pieces.
Grease tube pan and place bread sections in a circle pan.
Sprinkle pudding, cinnamon and nuts over bread dough.
Mix butter and sugar.
Cook until dissolved.
Pour over rolls.
Let rise in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Immediately invert on plate when done.

title: sugar-free peach-apple butter
directions: Peel and chop peaches.
Add juice.
Boil and mash until thick, 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: basic cookies
directions: Cream together the margarine and sugars and add the remaining ingredients.
Mix and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: creamy cheese pie
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping; blend thoroughly.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, about 4 hours. Serve topped with cherry pie filling.

title: sausage cheese crumbles
directions: Combine with hands and roll into small balls.
Bake at 400 degrees for 15 minutes.

title: out of this world pie
directions: Cook first five ingredients until thick.
Remove from heat and add gelatin.
Cool.
Add bananas and pecans.
Pour into baked pie shells.
Chill well and top with whipped topping to serve.

title: spiced tea
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Store mix in an airtight container.

title: noodles and ground beef
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef over low heat.
Add tomato sauce, salt and pepper; cook over medium heat for 15 minutes.
While meat mixture is cooking, bring 3 cups water to a boil in saucepan.
Add bouillon cubes, onion flakes, garlic powder and oregano.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Bring to a boil; add uncooked wide noodles.
Reduce heat and cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Combine noodle mixture with ground beef mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: granola
directions: Add first five ingredients, then milk, then oil.
Put in cake pan and bake at 300° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Remove; cool, then add 1 1/2 cups raisins.
Store in airtight container.
Great snack!
Also good on cereal, etc.

title: betty's swedish nut torte
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg yolks until light.
Add sugar and beat until thick.
Stir in pecans, crumbs and baking powder. Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into the batter.
Pour into a 9-inch cake tin that has been buttered and lined with waxed paper. Bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Turn out on a cooling rack and peel off waxed paper while very warm.
Combine butter, cocoa, powdered sugar and cream, making a smooth frosting.
Add coffee and extract.
Bottom side up, sprinkle the cake with a little powdered sugar and pipe a border of the frosting around the edges.
Serve in wedges.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: baked onions with sour cream
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place the unpeeled onions in foil-lined shallow pan.
Bake, uncovered, 1 1/2 hours.
Warm a heat-proof shallow pan.
When onions are tender, remove from oven.
Spear with fork, snip off both ends and remove skin.
Place onion in warmed dish.
Add butter and sour cream until melted.
Then add the rest of the ingredients and toss lightly.

title: eggnog cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat at medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Cool in pan for 10 minutes.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cook apricots in 1 cup of water for 15 minutes in covered pan. Drain, save 1/4 cup liquid.
In blender, combine apricots, liquid and sugar.
Blend until smooth.
Add the cream cheese, sour cream and nutmeg.
Blend again.
Spoon into bowl, cover and chill.

title: peanut butter crunch cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until crumbly with mixer on low speed. Save 2/3 of a cup for topping.
To remainder add egg and water; mix thoroughly.
Spread batter in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put reserved crumbs then chocolate chips over the batter. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: magic baked-on topping(for 9-inch square pan)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine ingredients in a small saucepan. Cook and stir until sugar melts.
Spread on top of warm baked cake.
Bake at 375°
for 10 to 12 minutes until lightly browned.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Put
ingredients
into a mixing bowl in order given and mix well.
Put	in
an	8
x 8-inch buttered and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions.
Cut tomatoes into wedges.
Cut green pepper into large pieces.
In separate bowl, mix salt, pepper, celery seed, sugar, salad oil and vinegar.
Pour over vegetables and soak overnight in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin crusty
directions: In a greased 13 x 9-inch pan, spread pumpkin pie mix. Sprinkle cake mix over pumpkin. Melt oleo and dribble over that. Add nuts on top.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: puff pastry sandwiches
directions: Thaw puff pastry sheets.
Cut each sheet into 6 pieces.
Roll each piece into a square.
Saute chicken and onions in butter.
On each piece of dough, place a slice of ham, some of the chicken and onion mixture and the 2 cheeses.
Roll each square, sealing the edges.
Bake on an ungreased baking sheet at 450° until puffed and golden brown.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and the butter (melted). Sprinkle confectioners sugar over the crumbs.
Press in pan and refrigerate.

title: butterscotch cake
directions: Mix together and put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put half of 12 ounces chocolate chips and nuts in mix.
Top with other half of chips and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes, until done.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Add packed brown sugar and beat well. Blend in egg, vanilla, sour cream, flour and soda.
Mix well. Stir in rhubarb.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan, greased.
Combine 1/3 cup brown sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pineapple caramel cake
directions: Mix sugar, flour, salt, soda and canned pineapple.
The juice from the pineapple can is the only liquid in recipe.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13 cake pan.
Top with the brown sugar and walnuts. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Mix flour and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to buttermilk, then add to flour mixture. Knead.
Make into biscuits.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400° to 425°. Store dough in refrigerator.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix beaten eggs with sugar and salt, stirring until dissolved. Stir in syrup and melted margarine; mix well.
Stir in the pecan halves.
Put into 9-inch pastry pie crust.
Cover edge with foil. Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil; bake about 25 minutes more or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on rack.
Cover and chill to store.

title: great burgers
directions: Mix all together, make into patties and brown.
Put into cake pan(s).
Mix cream of mushroom soup with milk and pour over hamburgers.
Simmer for 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: chocolate layered dessert
directions: Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mix and beat with whisk.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in 2 cups of the whipped topping.

title: mom's shrimp creole
directions: Put shrimp in kettle of boiling water.
Simmer 5 minutes. Drain.
Saute onions, pepper and celery in oil until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer 45 minutes.
Add shrimp; heat thoroughly and serve over rice.

title: easy pita chalupas(quick and easy)
directions: Spread pita round with refried beans.
Top with cheese and picante sauce.
Heat in microwave until cheese melts.
Top with guacamole and enjoy.
Serves 6.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add all other ingredients, except Fritos.
Add water to desired thickness.
Pour over Fritos in a bowl and enjoy.

title: pistachio pie
directions: Mix flour, butter and pecans and press into pan and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Whip cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar and spread on top of baked crust.
Whip pie filling and milk; spread on top of other.
Sit in icebox to chill.

title: spanish rice(ingredients to make 2 pounds of rice)
directions: Saute onions and garlic in about 10 to 13 tablespoons oil (1/2 olive oil okay). Add oregano, sason, tomatoes, tomato sauce and Alcaparradoes (drained).
Simmer a few minutes to let flavors mix.
Add rice and cans of beans (no draining needed) and water to make thick soupy consistency. Add salt to taste.

title: shrimp mold dip
directions: Soften gelatin in 2 tablespoons cold water; heat soup and add gelatin and other ingredients.
Place in a mold and chill.
Serve with rye bread.

title: turkey-stuffed peppers
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Halve peppers lengthwise; remove seeds. Blanch 5 minutes in a large pot of boiling water.
Drain, cut side down, on paper towels.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars together.
Add eggs and beat well. Mix in remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes.

title: meringue for coconut pies
directions: Beat egg whites in large mixing bowl until stiff. Add cream of tartar, sugar and vanilla. Beat with electric mixer again until well mixed. Pour on tops of 2 pies. Sprinkle top with coconut. Place in oven until golden brown. Remove from oven and cool. This recipe is enough for 2 pies.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and butter.
Press into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Next, put a layer of chocolate chips and a layer of butterscotch morsels.
Sprinkle coconut over the mixture. Spoon Eagle Brand milk over the top of the mixture.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over the top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes (until everything is melted).

title: chinese chicken
directions: Sauce:
Mix all ingredients except chicken in a blender.
Best if you let set all night in the refrigerator.

title: busy day chili
directions: Brown meat in large skillet.
Remove and drain fat.
Saute onion in skillet until golden.
Return meat to skillet.
Add beans, tomato soup and seasonings.
Stir, cover and simmer for about 30 minutes.
Serve with rice and/or crackers.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix beef and pork thoroughly.
Saute onions.
Mix with meat and other ingredients.
Work mixture 3 minutes.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour.
Roll into small balls and saute in hot fat until brown. Add consomme plus 1 can water.
Cook slowly.
Thicken gravy before serving.

title: tuna delight
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in glass dish.
Cover with lid. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: creamy cocoa cheesecake
directions: Combine crumbs, 3 tablespoons sugar and margarine; press onto bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Combine softened cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar, cocoa and vanilla, mixing with electric mixer until well blended.
Blend in eggs; pour into crust.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Combine sour cream, 2 tablespoons sugar
and vanilla; carefully spread over cheesecake. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Loosen cake from rim of pan.
Cool; remove rim.
Chill.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together.
Add more orange juice if needed.
Beat with mixer until smooth.

title: lazy daisy cake
directions: Heat
tablespoons
butter and milk; add eggs, sugar, flour, baking
powder, salt and flavoring.
When almost baked spread
on top
tablespoons butter, cream, brown sugar and coconut.

title: cherry salad supreme
directions: Dissolve jello, sugar and salt in boiling water.
Drain cherries, reserving 3/4 cup of syrup.
Add syrup and lemon juice to gelatin.
Chill until thick.
Fold half of cherries into 1 cup of jello.
Pour into 1-quart mold.
Chill until firm.

title: potato salmon casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in casserole.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes or until crust forms on top.

title: bagel and pita chips
directions: Bagels:
Make 1/4-inch slices.
Brush with melted butter. Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Spread in single layer on cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend eggs, oil and sugar together.
Set aside.
Combine all dry ingredients.
Add zucchini and small amounts of dry ingredients to first mixture.
Continue to blend until smooth. Add nuts and raisins.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet slaw
directions: Grate cabbage into a large bowl.
Add pineapple.
Split grapes in half (or quarters) and remove seeds.
Add mixture and add enough mayonnaise to moisten.
(A small amount of vinegar may be added for a tart tasting slaw.)

title: corn pudding
directions: Butter
8 x 11-inch round baking dish.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: mom's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together eggs, sugar and oleo.
Sift flour and add baking powder and soda.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheet and flatten with a glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 12 minutes.
May also use for cut out cookies.

title: practically perfect cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix flour, baking soda and salt in bowl and set aside.
Use mixer to mix 2 sugars briefly at low speed. Add butter first at low speed, then high; beat until it's pale, light and very fluffy.
Add vanilla at low speed, then high for few seconds.
Add eggs at low speed, then high until it looks creamed. Add flour, baking soda and salt, 1/2 cup at a time, at low speed for 1 minute, then high speed for few seconds.
Scrape bowl down on sides; add chocolate chunks and nuts.
Mix at low speed approximately 10 seconds.
Put tablespoon of mix on double thickness ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 minutes in electric stove, 10 to 11 minutes in gas stove.

title: chocolate scotcharoos
directions: Bring sugar and corn syrup to a boil in 3-quart saucepan. Remove from heat.
Blend in peanut butter.
Add Rice Krispies. Press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over top of the Rice Krispies.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Cook sugar, corn syrup and cream in pot to soft ball stage. Take off stove and add the corn flakes, coconut and peanuts.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper.
Let cool completely.
Can be kept in refrigerator.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix Dream Whip as directed on box only add a little sugar. Beat into Dream Whip the cream cheese.
Prepare jello using 2 cups water and 2 cups juice from the fruit.
Chill to slither stage. Add jello to Dream Whip mixture and drained fruit.
Mix well.
Pour into large pan and freeze.
Before serving, cut into squares and place each square on lettuce leaves.
Allow to thaw slightly.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Drain the juices from the fruit into a saucepan.
Heat to boiling point and remove from heat.
Mix in the gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
When the gelatin has cooled, stir in the fruits, whipped topping and cottage cheese.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: miracle chocolate fudge frosting
directions: Combine above on low heat.
Stir until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Cool, stirring frequently, until spreading thickness is reached.
You may need to refrigerate to hurry the cooling process.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs together.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add bananas and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: easy pork chops
directions: Wash pork chops and line in Pyrex dish. Cover with dressing. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Serve with Jo-Jo potatoes and salad.

title: chocolate dipped strawberries
directions: Line small tray with waxed paper.
In small saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate with shortening, stirring until smooth. Dip tips of strawberries into chocolate.
Place on prepared tray. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: red snapper and rice dinner
directions: In a 10 or 12-inch skillet, combine contents of rice and seasoning packets from rice mix, water, wine, broccoli, carrots and half the lemon zest.
Heat to boiling over high
heat, stirring often; boil 1 minute.
Spread evenly in skillet.
Place snapper in a single layer on top of rice.
Sprinkle with remaining lemon zest and half the lemon juice.
Reduce heat to medium-low. Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until snapper flakes easily and rice is tender.
Sprinkle with remaining lemon juice and parsley.
tags: quick-cooking long grain and wild rice mix

title: garlic pretzels
directions: Toss all ingredients in oil and stir.
Repeat stirring 5 or 6 times over a 15 minute period.
Place on a cookie sheet in a 325° oven for 15 minutes.

title: candy apples
directions: Stir over low heat in medium saucepan until well blended. Cook without stirring until turns pale yellow like caramel.
Test in cold water.
Drop in.
Candy should form a stiff ball.
When ready, add red food coloring and 1 small bag cinnamon hearts. Stir until melted.
Dip washed apples with sticks in them.
Cool on buttered wax paper.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in dish. In separate bowl mix corn and flour with a fork. Add eggs.
Add milk, sugar and salt.
Pour in buttered casserole (deep dish).
Bake at 450° for about 20 minutes.
Check about 10 minutes after putting into oven; edges will begin to set. Fluff with a fork, loosening the edges. Continue cooking until set and slightly browned.
May mix ahead of time, but cook just before serving.

title: steamed cranberry pudding
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Add cranberries and pecans.
Turn into 6-cup buttered mold and cover.
Place on oven rack in pan of water.
Bring to a boil and cover pan.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Steam 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Let stand 10 minutes.
Unmold and serve with Eggnog Dessert Sauce. May be kept in fridge or frozen.

title: french silk pie
directions: Prepare baked pie shell or graham cracker crust.
Cream sugar and butter until very light and fluffy (do not underbeat).
Melt chocolate and blend. Blend in vanilla; beat until fluffy.
Beat in eggs one at a time.
Turn into pie shell and chill well before serving.

title: graham crackers treat
directions: Boil margarine, butter and sugar for 2 minutes.
Add nuts; pour over graham crackers, separated on cookie sheet with sides. Bake for 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan to wax paper immediately.

title: chicken peanut butter stir fry
directions: Wash, peel, and slice vegetables in thin slices or pieces. Heat oil in large skillet over medium to

high heat. Add vegetables and cook till tender, stirring constantly. Remove vegetables to another container; add chicken to hot skillet. Cook, stirring constantly. When pink is gone from chicken, return vegetables to skillet. Stir water and cornstarch together, add remaining ingredients, stirring to make a smooth sauce. Make a well in chicken and vegetables. Pour in sauce. Stir Fry an additional 2-3 min. till sauce thickens. Serve over rice. 6 Servings.

title: linguine with spicy clam sauce
directions: Bring a large pot of water to a boil.
Meanwhile, thinly slice the onion and put aside.
In a large skillet, melt the butter in the oil over medium heat.
Add the garlic and onion and saute until the onion is translucent and beginning to brown slightly. Add the flour and cook, stirring, until the flour is no longer visible.
Add the broth, red pepper flakes, black pepper and salt. Reduce the heat to medium-low and simmer for 5 minutes.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package. Pour batter into pan.
Mix remaining ingredients (except nuts). Drop by teaspoons onto batter.
(Optional: run knife through batter.)
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake until cake springs back when touched lightly or when wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sausage puffs
directions: Open crescent rolls and press two triangles together at perforation to make 8 squares.
Cut each square in half.
Butter each square with margarine and sprinkle with cheese and seasoning. Place uncooked sausage link on each square.
Roll sausage in dough. Slice into thirds.
Seal edges of dough.
Place sealed side down on cookie sheet.
Can use toothpicks to hold together, if desired. Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Watch carefully.

title: chili's seasoned pork chops
directions: Season one side of chops.
Brown chops with chili side down. Sprinkle side up with chili powder.
Brown other side.
Remove from pan.
Add cream of mushroom soup and can of water, stirring until simmering.
Add chops and cover.
Simmer about 30 minutes, adding more water if chops stick to the pan.

title: mom's molasses cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add 2 eggs and molasses. Alternate milk and next 4 ingredients.
Add more flour (enough to make dough firm enough to roll and cut).
Bake at 350°.
Watch closely as they burn easy.
Makes a large batch and works well for gingerbread boy cookies.

title: champagne salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Mix all ingredients together and freeze.

title: magnificent muffins
directions: Mix together all dry ingredients.
In another bowl, combine milk with egg and stir in oil or melted shortening.
Mix together all ingredients lightly until just moistened.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full of batter.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: homestyle meat loaf
directions: Combine tomato sauce, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard in a small bowl.
Set aside.
Combine egg, onion, crumbs, ground beef, salt and pepper in a large mixing bowl.
Add 1/2 cup of the tomato mixture and blend thoroughly.
Shape into oval loaf and place in an oblong baking dish.
Make a depression in the top of loaf. Pour remaining tomato sauce over meat.
Bake uncovered for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 250° or until center is done.
Cover meat and let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: garden casserole
directions: Grease a baking dish; place rice in bottom.
Cook broccoli, carrots, zucchini and beans in boiling salted water until tender, 5 to 7 minutes; drain.
Reserve 4 zucchini slices for garnish. Spoon vegetables over rice.
Combine soy sauce and Marinara Sauce; pour over vegetables.
Cover dish with foil and bake 30 minutes. Combine cheeses; sprinkle over casserole and continue baking until cheeses melt, about 5 minutes.
Garnish with zucchini slices and serve.

title: spaghetti
directions: Brown onion and pepper (bay leaf, if desired) in margarine or oil, adding salt and pepper.
Mix in hamburger until done.
Add garlic salt and oregano, then add canned tomatoes, tomato sauce and paste.
Add Worcestershire.
Mix together and cook on low flame, covered, for at least 1/2 hour while spaghetti is cooking.

title: company potatoes
directions: Peel and cook potatoes until tender. Drain and beat until fluffy. Add salt, sour cream and cream cheese, beating well. Put in large baking dish. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: lime jello mold
directions: Dissolve jello in heated pineapple juice.
Mix canned milk, cottage cheese and mayonnaise.
Blend together well.
Add pineapple, celery and jello mixture.
Add nuts.
Will be lumpy. Pour into mold.
Let set until firm before serving.

title: oven barbecued round steak
directions: Cut the meat into small serving pieces.
Heat oil in a large skillet and brown the meat over medium heat, 15 to 20 minutes. Transfer to an ungreased casserole.
Mix the remaining ingredients and pour over the meat.
Cover and bake in a 325° oven until tender, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: bread pudding
directions: Break buns up.
Mix other ingredients and pour over buns. Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Stir together dry ingredients.
Combine egg, milk, and salad oil.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Stir in cranberries and nuts.
Turn into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Remove from pan; cool on rack.

title: brunch egg casserole
directions: In bottom of greased 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish, combine plain croutons and Cheddar cheese.
Combine eggs, milk, prepared mustard, onion salt and pepper.
Mix until blended.
Pour over crouton mixture in casserole.
Cook bacon until crisp; drain and crumble.
Sprinkle over top of casserole and bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes or until eggs are set.
Garnish with bacon curls, if desired.

title: barbecued ham
directions: Put in crock-pot or simmer on stove until thick (3 or 4 hours).
Stir often so it doesn't stick to bottom of pan.

title: rocky road s'mores bars
directions: Beat margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add combined flour and crumbs; mix well.
Press onto bottom of greased 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and cut into bars.
Serves 2 dozen.

title: danish dessert
directions: Make Kool-Aid with 7 cups water.
Bring to a boil.
Mix sugar and Clear Jell; add remaining water.
Stir into Kool-Aid; cook until clear and thickened.
Remove from heat and add jello.
Chill. Add drained fruit or use fresh fruit.
This is very good to put on angel food cakes or puddings.

title: oven fried chicken thighs
directions: Wash chicken thighs; pat dry and set aside.
In a small bowl, beat egg and half and half.
In another bowl, combine the bread crumbs, potato flakes and garlic salt.
Dip chicken thighs in egg mixture and then roll thighs in crumb mixture.
Place chicken thighs in a baking pan.
Sprinkle with melted butter and oil. Bake at 400° for about 35 minutes.
Increase temperature to 450° and bake for another 10 to 15 minutes, depending on thickness of thighs, until chicken is tender and done to your liking.
Juices should run clear when pierced with a fork.

title: italian baked chicken
directions: Clean chicken and place in a baking dish.
Pour salad dressing over the chicken.
Sprinkle red pepper sauce next.
Dot with capers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot pepper relish(jalapeno chow-chow)
directions: Put all ingredients into food processor and chop up.
After everything is chopped up, put into big pan and let come to a full boil.
Cook about 10 minutes.
Put into hot jars and seal.

title: clam chowder
directions: Drain clams, reserving liquid.
Set the clams aside.
In a large kettle, combine clam juice, potatoes, carrots, onion, butter and water.
Cook over medium heat for 15 minutes or until the vegetables are tender.
Stir in soup, milk, salt and pepper; simmer until heated through.
Stir in clams.
Yield:
10 to 12 servings (3 quarts).

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Combine cake mix, cooking oil and eggs.
Mix well, then add chocolate chips and pecans. Using a teaspoon drop cookie dough onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 or 12 minutes.

title: quick banana pudding
directions: Combine sour cream, milk, cool whip and instant pudding. In a bowl, layer cookies, pudding, bananas.
Crush cookies on top.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Have butter soft.
Add sugar.
Cream together good.
Add flour and eggs and beat well.
Stir in buttermilk, vanilla and nutmeg. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in muffin cups.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: lois hayes' fudge pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 8-inch pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: haystacks(sugar-free cookies)
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Use ice cream scoop to form haystacks. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: susan's molasses cookies
directions: Melt shortening; cool.
When cool, add sugar, molasses and egg.
Sift dry ingredients and add to wet mixture.
Chill until stiff.

title: bubble bread
directions: Mix together sugar and cinnamon.
Roll bread into small balls. Dip in butter and then in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Place in Bundt pan.
Pour leftover butter and sugar and cinnamon mixture over bread.
Let stand 1 hour.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: special bars
directions: Bring to a bubbly boil the sugar and syrup.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Stir in cereal.
Press into an 8-inch square pan.
Melt together chips. Spread over cereal mixture. Cool and cut into squares.

title: ice cream topping
directions: Combine ingredients and bring to a boil over medium heat. Cook 5 minutes, stirring vigorously.
Remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Beat with rotary beater for 1 minute.
Store in refrigerator.

title: april's cranberry mustard
directions: In small bowl, whisk together all the ingredients until well blended.
Transfer to a jar.
Cover with lid; refrigerate.
Great on next-day Thanksgiving turkey sandwiches.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken with celery and onion, then debone.
Add soups. Let cook for 10 minutes.
Add spaghetti.
When almost done, add chicken back in.
Season while cooking chicken.
Makes a thick sauce with noodles.

title: a christmas recipe
directions: Place all ingredients in a home a few weeks before Christmas. Sprinkle the kids with secrets and allow to simmer.
Gradually add patience to mother as needed.
Add as much joy, laughter, love and faith as hearts will hold.
Garnish father with unpaid bills. Serve generous portions topped with the blessings and love of the Christ Child.
There will be plenty to go around and lots left over for yourself.

title: six weeks raisin bran muffins
directions: In a large bowl, blend oil, eggs and buttermilk.
Add Raisin Bran cereal.
Let stand until cereal softens.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add to liquid and mix well.
Fill greased muffin cups 2/3 full and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. Mixture can be kept covered in refrigerator 6 weeks.
Do not freeze batter.

title: pizza crust
directions: Dissolve yeast and salt in warm water.
Add and gently stir in 1 cup of flour and let stand 5 minutes.
Add the rest of flour, enough to make soft dough.
Mix and spread by hand in 2 (12-inch) round pizza pans.
Spread any spaghetti sauce, approximately 1/2 to 3/4 cup per pizza.
Spread sausage and hamburger on the sauce. Add assorted chopped onions, peppers, mushrooms, ripe olives, etc. and top with cheese.
If using pepperoni, place cheese on top of sauce and top with pepperoni.
Let stand for 5 minutes before cooking in oven at 400° to 450° until done.
Cut and serve hot. Don't let pizza set in pan to avoid soggy crust.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Make a cream sauce (use directions on cornstarch box).
Layer noodles, tuna, sauce and potato chips.
Make 2 layers.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: souper meat-n-potato pie
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 cup soup, ground beef, onion, egg, bread crumbs, parsley and seasonings.
Press firmly into a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; spoon off fat.
Top with mashed potatoes, remaining mushroom soup, cheese and bacon.
Bake 10 minutes or until done.

title: green salad
directions: Wash the romaine and tear into small pieces.
Wash the arugula and remove the stems.
Place romaine and arugula in a bowl with the scallions and toss.

title: strawberry pretzel jello
directions: Combine pretzels with butter.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes, cool.
Prepare jello with boiling water. Add frozen strawberries with jello.
Refrigerate until it starts to thicken.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip. Layer Cool Whip mixture on top of pretzels.
Top with jello. Refrigerate.

title: christmas crispies
directions: You will need wax paper sheets.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Beat cream cheese and butter until creamy.
Add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add vanilla and baking powder.
Add flour slowly, beating well after each addition.

title: girl scout cocoa mix
directions: Mix together thoroughly.
Use 3 tablespoons per cup of hot water.

title: "weight watchers"
directions: Cook hamburger, drain.
Cook rice and set aside.
After draining meat, add tomato sauce, chili mix and stir together. Put mixture into casserole dish and add cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Great with salad and French bread.

title: dump dessert
directions: Melt buttah in Pyrex dish.
Mix sugah and flour together. Blend in milk and vanillah.
Pore this in dish but don't stir. Add eny fruit but don't stir.
Bake at 350° til a golden brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: This recipe freezes well.

title: beef enchiliada's
directions: Brown and drain beef and onions. Mix Enchilada seasoning mix with meat and onion. Add tomato sauce, corn, and cheese. Microwave potatoes several minutes until a knife will go easily through them. Then peel and chop into small cubes and add to mixture and stir well. Then put just enough Enchilada sauce on bottom of pan so that they don't stick. Put mixture (a good size spoon) onto each tortilla and roll up and lay in pan with sauce. Then use the rest of the Enchilada sauce to cover tops of rolls and top with more cheese.

title: boiled icing
directions: Mix sugar and water.
Cook until forms soft ball in water (cold).
Beat egg whites and pinch of salt until peaks firm.
Pour syrup over egg whites.
Beat.
Add Marshmallow Creme and beat until spreading consistency.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer.
Cook noodles by box directions.
Mix together cheeses, sour cream and egg.
Layer noodles, sauce, cheese mixture, etc.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bev's oatmeal patties
directions: Mix and fry.
Serve with mushroom soup or cashew gravy as sauce.

title: apple casserole
directions: Mix together cheese, melted margarine, sugar, flour and vanilla; then set aside.

title: fried zucchini(italian squash)
directions: Wash zucchini; peel and slice into 1/4-inch slices.
Beat egg slightly with milk.
Dip squash in egg mixture, then in flour and fry in deep, hot oil until lightly browned.
Season with salt and pepper, then sprinkle with cheese.
Serve with meal.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate until cold before serving.

title: make ahead salad
directions: Bring to boil liquid and add jello.
Dissolve and add cream cheese.
Chill until thick and add rest of ingredients.
Place in long pan that has been sprayed with Pam.

title: frozen cranberry banana salad
directions: Drain pineapple (save juice).
Add bananas to juice.
Mix sugared cranberry and drained bananas; add pineapple and whipped cream.
Pour in a 13 x 9 dish and freeze.

title: salted peanut chews
directions: Combine cake mix, oleo and egg. Mix until crumbly. Press in ungreased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes until light golden brown. Sprinkle with marshmallows and bake 1 to 2 minutes more until marshmallows begin to puff. Cool while preparing topping.

title: pineapple icing
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix flour and sugar and add to eggs.
Add melted butter and lemon juice; beat well.
Fold in one tall can of undrained pineapple.
Cook slowly until thick.
Spread over yellow layered cake mix.

title: fried indian bread (poori)
directions: About 1 1/2 hrs. before serving:
In medium bowl stir flours, water, salt and 1 1/2 tsp. salad oil until blended (mixture will be dry).
In bowl, with hand, knead dough until it holds together and is smooth, about 10 minutes.
Shape dough into ball and place in greased bowl; cover with plastic wrap; let rest 10 minutes.

title: christmas candy(makes 24 servings.  prep time:  10 minutes.)
directions: Melt almond bark. Add Rice Krispies, nuts and marshmallows. Mix and drop onto waxed paper.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Mix well.
Slowly add salad oil, mixing well.
Add onions and refrigerate overnight.

title: english muffin bread
directions: Combine 3 cups flour, yeast, sugar and soda.
Heat milk and water until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add to dry ingredients; beat well.
Stir in rest of flour to make a stiff batter.
Spoon into two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans that have been greased and dusted with cornmeal.
Sprinkle tops with cornmeal.
Cover; let rise in warm place for 45 minutes.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 25 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool.
Slice when cool and toast to serve.

title: chocolate, chocolate, chocolate cake
directions: Mix with mixer until well blended; pour into Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool.
Sprinkle with 10x sugar.
Enjoy.

title: french onion rice
directions: In 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass Pyrex dish, melt butter in oven to a light brown color.
Do not burn.
Add next 4 ingredients.
Stir gently.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until moisture is absorbed. Delightful different rice dish.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, taco seasoning mix and olives.
Heat until thickened. Sprinkle 1 cup corn chips over bottom of pie crust.
Spoon meat mixture over corn chips.
Spread sour cream over meat mixture. Cover with cheese.
Sprinkle remaining corn chips over cheese. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve in wedges topped with shredded lettuce and chopped tomatoes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving 1/2 cup beet liquid.
In 2-quart saucepan, mix vinegar, sugar, cornstarch, salt and liquid until smooth.
Add butter.
Cook over low heat until thickened.

title: chicken asparagus casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts; cool and then break into pieces.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with asparagus.
Place chicken on top and sprinkle with tiny bit of salt and pepper.
Mix the other 4 remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken and sprinkle with 1 cup shredded Cheddar cheese.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients together by hand.
Form into bite size balls. Lay on a baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cinnamon twists
directions: Bring to boil the sour cream.
Add shortening, sugar, soda and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add unbeaten egg, then yeast.
Stir. Add flour.
Knead a little.
Cover with cloth for a few minutes. Roll out and cover with brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cut into desired shapes.
Let rise.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at about 400°.
Spread frosting over when done.

title: rice pudding
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat yolks.
Add sugar, salt, milk, vanilla and rice.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture.
Put in baking dish.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato spoon bread
directions: Scrub and grate potatoes; set aside.
Mix eggs and honey.
Add oil; mix until smooth.
Add grated potatoes, orange and lemon peel and mix well.
Add spices.
Butter a baking dish well.
Bake slowly for 1 hour at 325°.
Good hot or cold.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Add 2 eggs and beat well. Add flour, soda, bananas, salt, vanilla and buttermilk. Beat well. Add nuts. Stir mixture and pour in pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion.
Drain well.
In a casserole dish, mix ground chuck, mushroom soup and water.
Place frozen Tater Tots on top.
Bake at 450° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed sausage and spinach roll
directions: Roll pizza crust out to the edges of a well greased 9 by 13-inch baking dish.
Spread pizza sauce evenly over dough leaving a 1/2-inch border.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients over sauce. Roll up jelly roll style and place seam down to bake.
Bake for 25 minutes at 400 degrees.
Slice and serve.

title: baked beans
directions: Chop bell peppers and onion.
Mix all ingredients together in a baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until onion and peppers are done.
Serves about 6 people.

title: apple pan dowdy
directions: Arrange apple slices in baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients in large bowl.
Pour over apples evenly.
Bake at 375° about 30 minutes.
Top with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: smoke sausage dinner
directions: Slice and fry sausage.
Fry potatoes, onions and green pepper. Add rest of ingredients.
Fry until tender.

title: pollo con crema e funghi(chicken with cream and mushrooms perugia)
directions: Thoroughly wash and dry chicken pieces.
Salt and pepper and roll in flour.
Melt butter or margarine in skillet; brown each side of chicken.
Arrange chicken in deep baking dish.
In separate bowl, combine sour cream, cream of mushroom soup, Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour over chicken.
Press 2 bay leaves into mixture. Place sliced mushrooms on top.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve over rice or linguine pasta.

title: yellow squash pickles
directions: Chop peppers and onions; add to sliced squash.
Mix salt with vegetables and let stand three hours.
Drain.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cut up chicken in bite size pieces; place in large Pyrex dish. Boil eggs.
Slice over chicken.
Sprinkle with mushroom pieces and peas.
Mix flour with milk.
Pour over all in Pyrex dish. Heat broth with butter and soup.
Bring to boil.
Pour over all. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Let stand 5 or 10 minutes before serving.

title: upside-down chocolate pudding
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and 2 tablespoons cocoa. Add milk, shortening and vanilla. Mix only until smooth. Add pecans. Put in greased shallow 1-quart baking dish.
Pour 1 1/2 cups boiling water over top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in muffin tins for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's meat loaf
directions: Mix lightly, but thoroughly and shape into loaf. Place in shallow pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Let cool for 10 minutes and slice.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Layer the above ingredients in the order they are written and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken with sherry and mushroom sauce
directions: Season chicken and brown in margarine. Arrange chicken in baking pan.

title: punch
directions: Pour gelatin into boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients, except ginger ale.
Chill.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: teriyaki wings
directions: Make marinade by combining all ingredients (except chicken) in a medium bowl.
Place chicken in a 9 x 14-inch baking dish.
Pour marinade over the wings; cover and put in refrigerator for at least 6 hours, turning occasionally.
Preheat oven to 375°. Arrange wings on wire rack in shallow roasting pan.
Bake 40 minutes, marinating twice and turning over once.
Makes 3 dozen pieces.

title: nutty date ball
directions: Mix the five ingredients together.
Serve with apple or pear slices or ginger cookies.

title: pinwheels
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Drain vegetables and blot dry on paper towels, mix with cream cheese mixture.
Spread on tortillas, roll tortillas tightly and chill at least 2 hours, cut roll into 1 inch pieces.
Makes 3 dozen - serve with salsa.

title: half leg of lamb
directions: With point of a sharp knife, prick the meat thoroughly.

title: german potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes and onion.
Add fried bacon which has been broken into small pieces.
Set aside.

title: blackberry wine pound cake
directions: Heat in microwave on Medium-low (should be thin). Pour 1/2 of mixture over hot cake just out of the oven. Let set in pan for 10 minutes. Turn cake out on plate and drizzle remainder of glaze over it. Cool and cut yourself a piece and enjoy it.

title: pumpkin chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat together sugar, pumpkin, oil and eggs.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly.
Add chocolate chips; stir gently.
Drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375°.
Done when touch does not leave an indention.
Makes a soft cookie.
Produces a large quantity.

title: blackberry cheese dip
directions: In a food processor, mix cheese, yogurt, jam and vanilla extract until smooth; add blackberries also.
Then chill until thick.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour water over 100% bran; let it stand.
In a very large bowl, cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add milk, then bran mixture.
Stir until blended.
Stir flour, soda and salt and add to mixture.
Mix well.
Add bran flakes and fold in until just moist. Add raisins or dates.
Chill for 1 day.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Keeps in refrigerator for 6 weeks.

title: little gumdrop cake
directions: Cream together the shortening, sugar, eggs and applesauce. Set aside. Sift together flour, cloves, cinnamon, soda and salt. Mix dry ingredients and creamed ingredients.
Add nuts, raisins and gumdrops.
Add vanilla. Bake in greased and floured 2 loaf pans or angel food cake pan for 1 hour in a 325° oven.

title: fried ice cream
directions: Dip ice cream in egg, then roll in crushed cookie crumbs. Repeat again.
Freeze at least 24 hours before frying.
Deep fry for 1 minute.

title: hot fudge sundae cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix flour, sugar, cocoa, baking powder, and salt. Combine oil, milk and vanilla; add to dry mixture, stirring well. Add nuts. Spread in ungreased 9 x 9 square pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar and cocoa. Pour hot water over batter. Bake for 40 minutes, let stand 15 minutes. Serve with ice cream.

title: asparagus pork tenderloins
directions: In skillet, brown medallions in butter or margarine; set aside.
In the same skillet, saute onion until tender and lightly brown.
Add milk and soup and blend well.
Return meat to skillet; cover and simmer 40 to 50 minutes or until tender.
When serving, top the meat with some of the sauce and serve the remaining sauce in a separate bowl.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix water and Jell-O and cool.
Add strawberries, bananas and pineapple.
Pour 1/2 mixture in square glass dish and gel.
Spread sour cream on top, then add remaining mixture and gel.
Great compliment for Christmas dinner.

title: pizza casseroles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown 1 pound ground beef.
Cook 7 ounces spaghetti noodles.
Mix 1/3 cup grated Parmesan cheese, 2 tablespoons melted oleo and 2 eggs (beaten).
Add noodles, ground beef and 1 large jar (32 ounces) Ragu.
Layer preceding mixture with Mozzarella cheese (3 or 4 cups) and 1 package pepperoni, topping it all with Mozzarella cheese, then pepperoni.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 20 minutes, then uncovered 15 minutes.

title: hospitality fruit cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spray miniature muffin pans with Pam. Fill pans 2/3 full and top with 1/2 of a red or green cherry, pressed down slightly.
Bake in preheated 300° oven for 30 to 35 minutes until lightly browned.
A pan of water placed on lower rack under cakes during baking will help prevent dryness.
When cool, store in layers of waxed paper in airtight tins.
Makes 48 miniature cakes.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Saute onions and garlic.
Add beans, chili sauce, mustard and syrup.
Pour into ungreased casserole.
Add 1 cup of grated Cheddar cheese and 1/2 cup buttered crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: citrus tea blend
directions: To serve:
Put one heaping teaspoonful of mixture in cup and pour in boiling water.
More can be used to add additional taste.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger lightly with onion.
Mix hamburger mixture, tomato sauce, tomatoes, salt, pepper, oregano and basil.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Cook 6 or 8 lasagna noodles; drain.
Stir in 1 tablespoon oil.
Mix cottage cheese and egg together.
Put 2 or 3 noodles in bottom of casserole dish.
Top with 1/3 of cheese mixture, then 1/3 of meat mixture.
Repeat twice.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese bubbles.
Allow to set before cutting.
Yield:
6 servings.
(If desired, add Mozzarella or other cheese in layering.)

title: cookie cut outs
directions: Cream together sugar and margarine.
Add the sour cream, vanilla and eggs.
(Best if all is beaten by hand.)
Then gradually add your flour, baking soda and salt mixture.
Chill for a few hours.
Roll out and use cookie cutters.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes at 325°.
Happy Baking!
Makes about 6 dozen.

title: fried whole turkey
directions: You also need large heavy pot and butane burner.

title: clams zuppa
directions: Bring all ingredients to rapid boil.
Wash quahaugs and add to sauce.
Bring to boil and then simmer approximately 30 minutes with lid on.
Pour over linguini.

title: harvard beets
directions: Heat beets and liquid together.
Combine cornstarch, sugar, salt, pepper and vinegar.
Stir into hot beets.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and thickened.
Serve hot.

title: frontier hominy
directions: Saute onions and pepper in 3 tablespoons margarine.
Add beef and cook just until pink disappears.
Add hominy, chili powder and tomato sauce.
Spoon into a 2-quart casserole.
Melt 2 tablespoons margarine in a small saucepan.
Stir in flour, milk and 1/2 cup cheese.
Cook, stirring constantly, until cheese is melted.
Pour over meat mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: mexican corn dip
directions: Mix well and chill overnight.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients. Pour into lightly greased shallow pan (9-inch square or larger). Bake, uncovered, at 400° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: leaf o' gold
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour loaf pans.
Measure all ingredients into large mixer bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat 3 minutes on high speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Pour into pans.
Bake 65 to 70 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine egg
yolks,
sugar and flour.
Mix well and add 1/4 stick
margarine and milk.	Cook until desired thickness. Layer sliced
bananas
and
vanilla wafers in ovenproof dish. Pour pudding over these.
Top with meringue.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: In saucepan, combine ketchup, steak sauce, syrup, vinegar, water, pineapple juice and horseradish. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.

title: barbecue or sloppy joes
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cook until tender.
Drain.

title: grandmother k's popcorn balls
directions: Combine sugar, water, vinegar, corn syrup and salt.
Cook to very hard ball stage (265°).
Add butter and pour over popcorn. Stir well with a knife.
Quickly form into balls with hands well-buttered.
Mixture will be hot.

title: macho nacho
directions: In a shallow baking dish, spoon chili over chips.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Heat in a microwave on High for 3 minutes or until cheese is melted and bubbly.
(Or heat oven to 450° and bake 10 minutes.)
Serves 4.

title: coleslaw salad
directions: Mix mayo, sugar, oil and vinegar.
Cut all vegetables and put in a big container with a lid.
Pour liquid mixture over vegetables and put lid on and shake to get all of the vegetables coated.
Let set for 2 hours in refrigerator and then serve.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes, peel and put in mixer bowl.
Add all of the ingredients except marshmallows and mix well.
Put mixture into casserole dish and bake at 350°for 20 minutes.
Top with miniature marshmallows.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Add the soup, water, half and half and chicken bouillon to the bacon and onion. Heat. I like to add 2 tablespoons cornstarch mixed with 2 teaspoons water. Add to the above the rice and cheese. Mix, heat and serve. Can add turkey, chicken or ham.

title: barbara padgett's chicken casserole
directions: Boil a whole chicken and remove bones (should be about 4 cups chicken).
Cook pepper and onion until tender but not brown in oleo.
In large mixing bowl, mix stuffing with broth.
Stir in eggs, celery soup, chicken, rice, onions, pepper and pimiento. Mix well.
Put into 13 x 9-inch baking pan and bake uncovered for 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: harvard beets
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and blend.
Add beet juice.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Add brown sugar, vinegar, salt, pepper and cloves.
Stir until sugar dissolves.
Add drained beets and heat thoroughly.

title: zucchini squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Spread in pan and bake until golden brown, 30 to 45 minutes.
Cut into small pieces to serve.

title: japanese pie
directions: Mix well and add 1/2 cup chopped pecans, 1/2 cup Angel Flake coconut and 1/2 cup raisins.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: fabulous bean dip
directions: Mix all ingredients (except Cheddar cheese) together in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
The last 15 minutes, put on cheese and leave uncovered.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in water; bring to boil.
Add broccoli to the boiling chicken broth and cook until somewhat tender.
For best tasting soup, I only use the flowerets.
Begin to warm the milk over medium heat.
Add the flour and pepper to melted butter, mixing well to form a thick paste.
After milk is warmed, add the butter and flour paste, stirring constantly until thickened (do not scald or allow to boil).
Add the white sauce to the broccoli (do not drain the water).
Then add the shredded cheese to the mixture.
Cook until soup has thickened.
Serves 6.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix 1/2 of onions and 1/2 Cheddar cheese with all other ingredients.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and put the remaining onions and cheese on top, then bake for 15 minutes.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix a bit of friendship with a bit of spite; add to it a bit of love.
Stir with all your might.
Then you add some luxury and a bit of toil; pour it in the pot of hate until it starts to boil. You'll improve the flavor and perhaps the taste if you add some prudence, carelessness and waste.
But should it be ill-flavored and seem spoiled a bit, strain the scum of worry off through the sieve of wit.
'Fore you start to dish it out, stir it up with strife.
And we highly recommend this recipe for life.
(Author: B.
R. King)

title: homemade oreo ice cream
directions: Beat egg yolks; add milk, water and vanilla.
Mix well.
Whip 1 pint whipping cream.
Crush 1 cup or more Oreo cookies.
Mix all together.
Freeze at least 6 hours in foil lined bread pan to be sliced or in a large covered bowl.

title: red lobster biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick, milk and Cheddar cheese.
Beat vigorously for 30 seconds. Drop by spoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake 10 minutes at 450°. Do not overbake.
Mix butter, Parmesan cheese, garlic powder and parsley.
Brush over hot biscuits before removing from pan.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Beat together milk and vanilla pudding.
Add Cool Whip.
Place graham crackers in bottom of 8 x 12-inch pan.
Cover with pudding mixture.
Add another layer of graham crackers.
On top of them spread 3/4 can dark chocolate icing.
Chill in refrigerator.
Can be made day ahead.
