(Half of recipe can be made in 7 x 7-inch pan.)

title: ham steak and cranberry-orange sauce
directions: Preheat browning dish according to manufacturer's directions. Place ham steak on preheated dish; cover with paper towel. Microwave at High 1 to 2 minutes.
Combine cranberry sauce, orange juice and horseradish.
Turn ham slice over; top with sauce mixture.
Microwave at High 2 to 3 minutes, or until sauce is hot. Makes 4 servings.

title: gooey butter coffee cake
directions: Melt butter and mix with cake and 2 eggs; mix by hand.
Press into lightly greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Next, soften or melt cream cheese and mix eggs and powdered sugar.
Pour on top (even) of first mixture, then sprinkle powdered sugar on top.
Take the 4 teaspoons of powdered sugar out of the box before adding it to the cream cheese and eggs.

title: pot roast seasoning mix
directions: Combine all ingredients and store in container.
Cover tightly.
Store in cool, dry place.
Use 1 tablespoon of mix per side of pot roast.
Makes enough for 3 pot roasts.

title: heath bar cake
directions: Stir sugar into flour and mix with pastry blender. Cut in margarine until fine. Measure out 1 cup and set aside. To rest of mixture, add egg, milk, soda, salt and vanilla. Beat well. Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan. Spread with topping. Break 6 toffee candy with hammer. Mix candy with 1 cup chopped nuts and reserved mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: the old red rooster
directions: In a freezer container, combine cranberry-apple drink, lemonade concentrate and rum flavoring. Freeze to an ice slush, about 3 hours. Spoon into tumblers. Serve with straws. Preparation time: 10 minutes.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry bacon, garlic, ground beef and celery until lightly browned.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer gently for 1/2 hour.
Remove bay leaf and garlic.
Combine tomato mixture with the rice, green pepper, mushrooms and onions.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 1 hour. About 10 minutes before removing from oven, scatter the diced cheese on top.

title: sweet 'n sour wiener bites
directions: Mix jelly and mustard in a chafing dish or double boiler. Heat, but do not boil.
Add cocktail wieners to heated sauce and keep hot.

title: bruschetta(toasted bread with tomatoes)
directions: Put diced tomatoes into a bowl with olive oil, garlic, hot pepper, basil and salt.
Mix well. Slice bread 1/2-inch thick and toast both sides.
Remove from toaster and place on serving tray. Place an equal portion of the tomato mixture on each slice.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: celery stuffing
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients thoroughly and stuff into celery, chill until serving time.

title: perfect microwave fudge
directions: Mix confectioners sugar and cocoa together in square (microwavable) glass pan.
Add milk and butter.
Cover with wax paper and microwave for 2 minutes on High.
Mix ingredients thoroughly and add chopped nuts and vanilla.
Mix again.
Chill for 1 hour before cutting and eating.

title: easy to do frozen pickles
directions: Mix all together until sugar is dissolved.
Put in Ziploc bags, seal and put in freezer.

title: chicken catrizinni
directions: Cut chicken breasts into pieces and cook.
Break spaghetti into pieces and cook.
Cut cheese into cubes.
Saute onions and pepper in butter; add broth, soup and mushrooms.
Stir; then add cheese and stir over a low heat until cheese is mostly melted. Add chicken and spaghetti.
Mix well.
Pour into large Pyrex dish. Heat for 30 minutes at 350°.
This freezes well.
This recipe will serve 12 people.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli cuts according to package directions.
Drain. Add Cheez Whiz and soup to cooked rice.
Add broccoli cuts and water chestnuts to rice mixture.
Bake at 350° to 400° until bubbly.

title: chili stew
directions: Brown ground beef and Italian sausage in a skillet; then put everything in a stock pot.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat to low and simmer for around 1 hour.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta.
Drain.
Put
in bowl and add chopped onion and French dressing.
Refrigerate 12 hours.
Next day, add the chopped vegetables (8 cups).
Just before serving, add olives and mayonnaise	to
taste.
Shrimp, sea legs or chicken may be added.

title: benoit's bannock(good stuff, especially with a pot of tea.)
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening and add enough water to make a soft dough.
Knead briefly and pat into a large greased frying pan, preferably cast-iron.
Bake at 375° about 30 minutes or until golden.
Break off chunks, butter liberally, and eat with honey, syrup or jam.

title: coca cola cake
directions: Sift flour, and sugar in a bowl and set aside.

title: easy hot apple betty
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.
Serve warm with cream or vanilla ice cream.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: crab stuffed mushrooms
directions: Rinse mushrooms in cold water; dry.
Remove and chop stems. Blend flour and seasonings into butter.
Add cream gradually. Cook until thick and smooth, stirring constantly.
Add mushroom stems, parsley and sherry.
Mix well.
Stir in crab meat.
Stuff mushrooms.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake on greased baking sheet at 350° for
15 minutes.

title: smiles(method:  fireless)
directions: Wash apples; cut into wedges.
Spread a thin coat of peanut butter on one side of each wedge.
Place 6 or 8 mini marshmallows on half of the wedges.
(Think of the skin of the apple as lips and the marshmallows as teeth.) Top with a wedge of apple.
Fill in between the "teeth" with chocolate chips.
(The chocolate chips are the cavities!)

title: veal chops with tomatoes
directions: Season chops with salt and pepper as desired.
Dip first in egg and then in crumbs.
Refrigerate 15 minutes to set crumbs. Heat oil in a medium pan and saute garlic 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes and marjoram and simmer 15 minutes.
In another pan, saute chops in oil and butter until golden.
Serve chops with the sauce, noodles and a loaf of crusty bread.
Serves 4.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples in pan with spices and sugar. Mix 1 cup of flour, 1/2 cup butter and 1 cup brown sugar until coarse. Then put on apples. Bake at 325 degrees until golden brown.

title: ham-cheese crescent pinwheels
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheet; unroll crescent dough and seal perforated seams.
Place ham slices on dough. Spread with mustard and sprinkle with grated cheese and seal edges.
Roll like jelly roll; cut into 18 slices, about 3/4-inch each and place on baking sheet.
Place seeds on pinwheels as desired.
Bake until lightly browned, about 12 minutes.

title: momma's pineapple pie
directions: Chill evaporated milk in an ice tray in the freezer until soft crystals form (about 15 to 20 minutes).
Whip until stiff (1 minute).
Add lemon juice.
Continue whipping until very stiff (about 2 minutes).
Fold whipped milk into chilled jello.
Fold 1 cup well drained crushed pineapple into whipped mixture.
Spoon into crust and chill 2 hours or until firm.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash; boil until done and mash.
Add all other ingredients except cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes. Add cheese last 5 minutes.

title: pork chop rice casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in small amount of oil on both sides.
Place uncooked rice in bottom of casserole dish.
Place browned pork chops on top of rice.
Mix the two soups together and pour over pork chops and rice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: gingerbread and butterscotch sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until thickened, stirring frequently.
Sauce thickens as it cools.
Stir well before using.

title: oriental chicken casserole
directions: Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 40 minutes or until hot. Put noodles on top.
Serves 10 to 12.
Can be halved.

title: herb cream cheese spread
directions: In a food processor or blender, process all ingredients for 10 seconds. Transfer to a glass bowl; cover and refrigerate for at least 1 hour to allow flavors to blend. Serves 8 (2 tablespoons per serving).

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook ziti and drain.
In large bowl combine cooked ziti, 1 1/2 cups spaghetti sauce, Ricotta cheese, Mozzarella cheese, parsley, egg, oregano, garlic powder and pepper.

title: shrimp crabmeat casserole
directions: Simmer onion, pepper, celery, mushrooms and juice until tender, but not brown (about 3 minutes). Add crabmeat, shrimp, mayonnaise, salt, pepper, Worcestershire sauce and melted butter. Mix and put in casserole dish. Cover with crumbs and bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: shoestring salad
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients and chill. Just before serving, add shoestring potatoes and serve immediately.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan on top of stove.
Add milk, then sugar.
Bring to a boil; boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat, then add vanilla, peanut butter, cocoa and oats.
Stir well. Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Cool in the refrigerator; they will harden.

title: turtle cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt caramels, butter and milk in a double boiler, set aside.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Pour half the batter into a greased and floured oblong pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Remove cake from oven and pour caramel mixture over top. Next sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over caramel layer.
Now pour rest of cake batter on top and bake for 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.
Cool cake 20 minutes before serving.
Spoon a generous amount of Cool Whip on top when serving.

title: frozen strawberry dessert
directions: Mix together flour, brown sugar, margarine and nuts.
Make like a pie crust and press into a pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: gumbo
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; add flour, saute onion and celery. Cook until light brown.
Add okra and cook about 30 minutes.
Stir often while cooking.
Stir in tomatoes and gradually add hot water and tomato liquid.
Add bay leaves, crab, shrimp, oysters, parsley, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour, stirring often.
The file powder is stirred into gumbo just before serving. Serves 4 to 6.

title: salmon nuggets
directions: In a saucepan, melt butter and in it, saute onion for 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, gradually stir in milk and cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and beat in salt, pepper and egg yolks.
Stir in salmon and fresh bread crumbs.
Chill.
Shape mixture into 2-inch nuggets, roll in flour and dip in egg mixture and coat with dry bread crumbs.
Fry in hot deep fat (375°) for 4 to 5 minutes or until golden brown. Drain on paper towel.
Serve piping hot with favorite cream sauce. Serves 4.

title: cherry trifle
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water; refrigerate 1 hour.
Cube cake into 1-inch pieces.
Layer in trifle bowl 1/2 of cake, 1/2 jello, 1/2 pie filling, remaining 1/2 of cake, jello and pie filling.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: date pillow
directions: Stir all ingredients together except whipped cream and 1/4 of cracker crumbs.
Shape into a pillow or a roll and roll in reserved crumbs.
Wrap in several thicknesses of wax paper and store in refrigerator.
Good topped with whipped cream when served.

title: walnut-raisin bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg and juice; beat well.
Add 1/3 cup flour mixture and beat until smooth.
Mix in rest of flour and pineapple.
Stir in raisins and walnuts.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch baking pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cool jello salad
directions: Bring first 3 ingredients to boil.
Allow to cool!
Not jell! Beat cream cheese and Cool Whip together.
Add milk.
Add chilled Jell-O mix.
Beat well!!
Chill.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Wash dried beans.
Remove any foreign matter.
Place in 4 to 6-quart saucepan.
Add 4 quarts water, ham, onion, garlic and seasoning.
Simmer slowly about 3 hours, until beans are soft and gravy is thick.
Serve over cooked rice with Tabasco sauce.

title: easy onion dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine ingredients and mix well. Chill to blend flavors.
Stir before serving.
Serve with fresh vegetables or potato chips. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chicken breasts in cream
directions: Cut chicken breasts into 4 serving pieces.
Brown breast in fat until golden brown.
Heat onion, garlic, broth, cream and seasonings in saucepan.
Place chicken in roaster and pour sauce over them.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 375°.
Uncover and bake 15 to 20 minutes more.
Remove chicken from pan and keep warm while making gravy.

title: zucchini pancakes(low in fat and cholesterol)
directions: Combine zucchini, onions and egg.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to zucchini mixture.
Mix well.
Drop spoonfuls on mixture into heated oil in skillet.
Fry until brown and crisp on edges.
Makes 10 to 12 pancakes.
Has approximately 50 calories per pancake.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except butter and cracker crumbs.
Combine butter and cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Serves 4 people.

title: potato latkes
directions: Preheat oven to 475°.
Peel or scrub potatoes and cut into long strips about 1/2-inch wide.
Dry strips thoroughly on paper towels.
Toss in a bowl with oil as if making a salad.

title: crab meat with english muffins
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients; spread on the English muffins. Put a dash of paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut in smaller pieces and serve.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown meat; remove from skillet.
Lightly saute onions in butter in the same skillet; add remaining ingredients.
Cook on low.
Simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
Return meat to skillet and continue simmering until hot.
Serve on spaghetti noodles.

title: hot dog relish
directions: Bring to rolling boil.
Simmer 3 minutes.
Place in prepared jars and seal.

title: heidi's tart garlic marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan and simmer 10 minutes. Store in refrigerator. Use with steak or poultry. Makes about 4 cups.

title: sugarless freezer date cookies
directions: Beat margarine, egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt and add to first mixture.
Add dates, coconut and nuts. Form dough into two 1 1/2-inch rolls.
Wrap in wax paper and chill until firm.
Slice into 3/8-inch slices and place on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Will keep in fridge for a month.

title: cajun cake
directions: Mix ingredients and bake in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Cook vegetables; drain.
Add 3/4 stick oleo and small box of Velveeta cheese; stir until melted.
Crush Ritz crackers.
Add melted oleo.
Put corn mixture in casserole dish and sprinkle cracker mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: copper pennies
directions: Slice carrots diagonally.
Cook until tender.
Slice onion. Slice pepper in thin strips.
Place onion and pepper on top of carrots while cooking to soften.
Boil remaining ingredients until sugar dissolves, not any longer.
Pour over vegetables while hot. Cool.
Will keep in refrigerator 2 to 3 weeks.

title: macaroni and sausage bake
directions: Cook macaroni according to package.
Cook sausage and onion until browned.
Drain off excess fat.
Combine sausage mixture, macaroni, soup, milk, eggs and cheese.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberries, pineapple and sugar together.
Fold in marshmallows.
Let stand at least 2 hours (overnight is better). Fold in Cool Whip shortly before time to serve.

title: gingerbread men
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Mix in dry ingredients and syrup until dough.
Knead with hands; roll on floured board.
Cut out currants for eyes.
Bake in a greased pan at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: brenda lee's pretzel salad
directions: Assemble all ingredients and utensils. Combine crushed pretzels, sugar and margarine and spread in a 9 x 13 pan. Bake for 10 minutes in a 325° oven. Set aside to cool.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: Cream together 1/2 pound sugar, butter and vanilla until fluffy.
Add remaining sugar, marshmallow and peanut butter.
Mix well.
Shape into eggs, then chill, overnight if possible.
Coat with milk chocolate.
Melt 2 large Hershey candy bars in double boiler and add 1/2 bar paraffin grated into chocolate.

title: key lime pie
directions: Whip up one whole egg, then add the 3 yellows, can of sweetened milk and the juice.
Pour into the pie shell.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: brisket donjunair
directions: Trim brisket.
Season with Season-All; wrap in aluminum foil. Cover completely.
Put in oven and let cook at 375° for 1 hour. Cut and let sit for 1/2 hour.
Take juice from meat and make sauce with butter and flour.
Bring to boil.
Add tomato paste,
onion, carrots and green pepper.
Saute until cooked.
Use as garnish over meat.
Pour sauce over meat and serve.

title: chicken cobbler
directions: Put margarine in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish and set in oven at 350° until melted.
Mix chicken, rice and broth; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Pour this mixture into casserole. Spoon chicken into center.
Bake about 50 minutes at 350°. Serve.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In medium sized bowl, blend together condensed milk, lemon juice, lemon peel and egg yolks until thickened.
Turn into pie shell.

title: ham, split pea and black bean soup(merlyn's marvelous medley)
directions: Leave generous portions of ham on ham bone; cook on low for several hours in water in Dutch oven.
Refrigerate in liquor for 1 or 2 days.
Remove; cut up leftover ham in chunks.
Simmer again in liquor, adding split peas.
After 1 hour, add beans and rice. Cook on low; as mixture thickens, add chunks of onion.
Simmer until soup is soft.
Can be served on noodles or biscuits.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and oleo.
Boil 5 minutes, no longer.
Remove from heat.
Add soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Pour over corn and mix quickly.
Bake, uncovered, at 200° for 1 hour.
If using butter, bake at 150°.

title: colonel sanders chicken
directions: Make paste of first 5 ingredients.
Brush to coat chicken. Evenly stack pieces in bowl.
Cover and refrigerate several hours. One and one-half hours before serving, heat 2-inches of oil in a 9-inch pot to 425°.
Dip pieces in milk, then in pancake mix; coat well.
Dust off excess.
Lightly brown about 4 minutes each side. Place in shallow pans.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: hungarian chicken paprika
directions: Boil chicken parts
for 35 minutes.
In two frying pans, divided equally
add
vegetable
oil,
garlic (finely chopped), tomatoes (finely
chopped),
water,
chicken bouillon, salt and pepper.
Bring to
a boil.
Lower flame, strain chicken, add to pans equally and cover, simmer for 20 minutes.
Turn off flame, remove from heat.
Remove chicken from pans.
Add 16 ounce sour cream to each
pan
and
stir until well blended.
Serve cooked noodles or dumplings, topped with chicken and pour sauce generously over entire dish.

title: cream cheese-ginger ale salad
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, sugar and lemon juice. Soften gelatin in cold water. Add hot water to gelatin. Add gelatin mixture to creamed mixture. Add ginger ale. Chill until the consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Fold in fruits.
Pour into lightly greased mold (Pam or mayonnaise) and refrigerate until set.

title: sugar-free fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit. Sprinkle dry jello over fruit. Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Refrigerate.
May use different flavors of jello.

title: heavenly ham salad
directions: Prepare Creamettes medium shells according to package directions; drain.
Combine shells, ham, celery, radishes and cucumber.
Blend together mayonnaise, yogurt, mustard and garlic salt.
Toss dressing with salad mixture.
Serve immediately or cover and chill.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Garnish as desired. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: matthew schmidt's m&m's cookies
directions: Blend shortening and sugars.
Beat in vanilla and eggs.
Sift remaining dry ingredients together.
Add to sugar and egg mixture; mix well.
Stir in 1 cup M&M's.
Reserve remaining candies for decoration.
Bake at 350° until done for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Place shortening, salt and vanilla extract in mixing bowl. Beat at speed 5 until blended, about 30 seconds.
Add sugar, gradually continuing to beat, until thoroughly creamed, about 2 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating at speed 5 until well blended, about 1 1/2 minutes.
Sift together flour, cinnamon and baking powder.

title: salmon patties
directions: Combine salmon, egg and onion.
Stir in flour.
Stir baking powder into salmon liquid; add to salmon and onion mixture.
Form mixture into 6 patties.
Heat shortening in skillet and fry patties on each side until golden brown.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Soften the gelatin in cold water.
In a medium saucepan, combine the beaten egg yolks with 1/2 cup of the sugar, the pumpkin, milk, salt and spices.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until the mixture begins to thicken.
Remove from the heat and stir in softened gelatin.
Stir well and allow to cool.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Drain Veg-All and water chestnuts; place in a 3-quart mixing bowl.
Add chicken soup, chopped onions, cheese and mayonnaise. Mix well.
Pour into 2 or 3-quart casserole; top with buttered crumbs, chips or herb dressing.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until bubbly and topping is brown.

title: herbed shad with edible bones
directions: Wash and dry shad.
Sprinkle inside with lemon and pepper. Place fish on rack in baking pan.
Add liquid to a level just below fish.
Add rest of ingredients.
Cover tightly.
Let steam in a 350° oven for 5 hours.
Baste frequently.
Serves 6.

title: holiday party dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients except fresh vegetables; mix well. Cover; chill. Stir before serving. Garnish with additional green onion, if desired. Serve with vegetables. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: cream sauce for pasta recipes
directions: Heat and melt margarine at low heat.
Stir in flour until smooth.
Gradually add chicken broth and simmer until thick.
Add milk gradually.
Add cheese and season to taste.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine softened cream cheese with onion, Miracle Whip and milk.
Cut shrimp in small pieces and add with remaining ingredients.
Mix well and chill before serving.

title: peanut butter salad
directions: Peel and dice apples and celery and remove any strings.
Chop nuts.
Add all ingredients together.
The consistency should be like potato salad.
Serve on top of a slice of lettuce.

title: busy day chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash fryer and cut into serving pieces. In an ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch Pyrex pan, cover bottom with rice. Lay chicken on top of rice one layer thick.
In bowl, mix chicken and onion soup together, rinsing both cans with 1/2 can of water to make 1 cup of water.
Add water to soups.
Mix well and pour over chicken and rice.
Cover tightly with foil and place in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix well.
Better if it sits overnight.

title: quick fruit cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar; add cherry juice, vanilla and flour and beat on low.
*Save 1/2 cup flour to roll all fruit and nuts, except coconut.
Fold together.
Bake in 250° oven for 2 hours.

title: pumpkin flan
directions: Sprinkle 1/2 cup sugar into a small heavy skillet.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly with a wooden spoon until sugar melts and turns light brown.
Pour caramel syrup into a 8-inch round cake pan coated with cooking spray, tilting pan to coat evenly.
Set aside (caramel syrup will harden).

title: mulled cider
directions: Heat in crock-pot from 2 to 5 hours.

title: poor man's steak
directions: Combine all ingredients except soup.
Shape into small narrow loaf.
Wrap loaf in foil and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, slice loaf into 1-inch slices.
Flour on both sides.
Fry in oil until browned.
Place fried meat in baking dish, 9 x 13-inch.
Top with soup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes own gravy that is good over baked potatoes.

title: cherry tomatoes
directions: Mix together and beat thoroughly.
Slice cherry tomatoes in half and scrape out centers.
Fill with stuffing.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: sausage rolls
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
Mix raw sausage, cheese and Bisquick and form into small balls.
Bake on cookie sheet 20 minutes at 350°.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of electric blender. Process until smooth. Use immediately or refrigerate.
Equivalent to 1 can Eagle Brand sweetened condensed milk.
This recipe is a real money saver!
Pass it to your friends.

title: first place chili
directions: Heat the oil in a heavy pot over medium heat.
Add the onions, bell pepper, celery and garlic.
Cook, stirring until the onions are translucent.
Add the meat to the pot a little at a time, stirring occasionally, until the meat is evenly browned.
Stir the remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer, uncovered, for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Stir often.
Taste and adjust seasonings.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Heat cheese and cream in saucepan until cheese is melted. Arrange half the potatoes in buttered 9 x 13 x 2-inch glass pan, overlapping the potatoes.
Pour half the cheese mixture over them. Arrange remaining potatoes and pour remainder of cheese over them. Bake at 400° until golden brown, approximately 1 hour. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: orange date muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a bowl, combine the dry ingredients. Combine eggs, orange juice and butter; mix well.
Stir into dry ingredients just until moistened.
Fold in dates, walnuts and orange peel.
Coat muffin cups with nonstick cooking spray or use paper liners; fill 2/3 full with batter.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool for 5 minutes before removing from pan to a wire rack.

title: rocky road fudge
directions: Line an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan with foil.
Set pan aside. In a mixing bowl, combine powdered sugar and cocoa powder.
Mix well with a wooden spoon and set aside.
In a small saucepan, mix margarine or butter and milk.
Put pan on burner.
Turn to low. Heat and stir until margarine melts.
Turn off burner; take pan off burner.
Pour melted margarine or butter mixture over powdered sugar mixture.
Stir with the wooden spoon until smooth.
Add marshmallows, nuts and vanilla; stir well.
Pour into foil-lined pan.
Spread evenly with a rubber scraper.
Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.
Makes 36 pieces.

title: farmhouse barbecue muffins
directions: Separate biscuits. Flatten into 5-inch circles.
Place each in muffin tin and flatten to make cup. Set aside.
Brown beef and drain.

title: chili cheese souffle
directions: Remove crust and tear bread into cubes.
Beat together eggs and milk.
Strain and wash chilies.
Melt butter.
Rub 3-quart casserole or pan with butter.
Layer 1/3 bread in casserole, 1/2 chili over bread and 1/2 cheese over chili.
Layer bread, chili and cheese and end with bread on top.
Pour eggs, milk and butter evenly through it.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight. Remove 1 1/2 hours before baking at 400° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: water chestnuts and bacon
directions: Cut bacon in half and wrap chestnuts with bacon; secure with toothpicks.
Mix ketchup, peaches and sugar; pour over bacon wrapped chestnuts and drain grease.
Bake at 350° for thirty minutes.
May be frozen for later use.

title: linguini with clam sauce
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add the other ingredients and bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes.
Cook linguini noodles and drain.
Immediately toss sauce with noodles.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients together well.
Form into 2 loaves and place in greased casserole.
Put strips of raw bacon on tops of loaves and pour 2 cups tomato juice over.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and at 325° for 2 hours, uncovered.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream shortenings.
Add sugar and beat until smooth.
Add egg yolks and beat well.
Combine flour and soda and add alternately with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla, coconut and nuts.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into three greased and floured 8 or 9-inch pans. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: party potatoes
directions: Mix melted butter with onion, Cheddar cheese, chicken soup and sour cream.
Mix with hash browns.
Mix 1 stick margarine with corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crush cookies.
Put some aside to sprinkle top of dessert with.
Combine remaining cookies and margarine.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
Mix half of Cool Whip and all of the cream cheese until smooth.
Spread over cookies and freeze. Prepare pudding as directed; spread over Cool Whip mixture. Spread remaining Cool Whip over pudding.
Sprinkle crushed cookies on top.
Refrigerate.

title: country style barbecue pork chops
directions: Brown chops; season with salt and pepper and place in a baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over chops.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Turn occasionally.
Great with boneless pork, spareribs and boneless chicken tenders or breasts.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix water, sugar, salt and shortening together and cool to lukewarm.
Soften yeast in like warm water and stir in first mixture.
Add eggs, stir in 4 cups of flour.
Beat until smooth and add rest of flour until it makes a fairly stiff dough.
Grease bread loaf and let rise, covered.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in tightly covered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 3 hours.
Don't open oven while cooking.

title: virginia apple pudding
directions: Mix and bake in same dish.
Melt butter in 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine next 6 ingredients to make batter; pour on margarine.
Drain apples; pile in center of batter.
Bake at 375° until batter covers fruit and crust browns for 30 to 40 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: tea scones
directions: In a bowl, combine the flour, baking powder, sugar, soda and salt.
With pastry blender, cut butter into the flour mixture. Add currants.
Gradually add the buttermilk until the dough clings together.
Turn dough onto lightly floured board.
Pat or roll into a round shape, 1/2-inch high.
Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place on greased or ungreased cookie sheet.
Brush tops with cream.
Bake for 15 minutes in a 450° oven.
Serve warm. Makes 18.

title: reeses pieces
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; press into pan.
Melt chocolate chips; spread over top.
Cut into squares before freezing.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine oil, eggs and sugar.
Add apples and pecans.
Add flour and soda; stir well.
Add vanilla.
Pour into three waxed paper lined cake pans.
Place in cold oven.
Set temperature at 325°.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Chop cranberries in a food processor, add sugar and let sit for several hours.
Add chopped apple and crushed pineapple only, reserve juice and add pecans.

title: company potatoes(serves 6 to 8)
directions: Set oven at 325°.
Use 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: olive nut spread
directions: Mash 6 ounce of softened cream cheese (room temperature) with a fork, then add 1/2 cup mayonnaise.
Blend well.
Stir in 1/2 cup chopped pecans and 1 cup chopped salad olives.
Now add 2 tablespoons olive juice and a dash of pepper, but no salt.
Stir well.
This mixture will be slightly mushy, but it's supposed to be that way.
Put it in a covered container and refrigerate for several hours and it will become firm.
This delicious spread is great on thin toast.
Makes good finger sandwiches.

title: hot whiskey sauce
directions: Bring milk to a boil.
Stir cornstarch into sugar; whisk with egg substitute and bourbon in a small bowl until smooth.
Blend into hot milk and simmer, but do not boil, for 5 minutes.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash; drain.
Combine next 5 ingredients and mix with squash.
Pour into greased casserole (large) and top with cracker crumbs.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: velvet pear salad
directions: Mix jello and water in blender.
Pour into bowl.
Mix pears and syrup, cream cheese and lemon juice in blender.
Add to first ingredients and stir.

title: anne's quick sweet rolls
directions: Lay frozen dinner rolls around the bottom of a generously greased bundt pan.
Sprinkle dry pudding mix and pecans on top of rolls.
Combine butter and sugar and pour over pecans.
Let rise until dough reaches top of pan (can let rise overnight for breakfast).
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.
Turn onto a serving dish immediately.

title: make ahead breakfast
directions: Place 4 slices of bread in casserole dish.
Mix sausage and mustard.
Spread over bread.
Sprinkle 1/2 grated cheese.
Top with other 4 slices of bread, then cheese.
Mix eggs, milk and seasonings.
Beat slightly and pour over casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until fluffy and brown.

title: bagel dip
directions: Add all ingredients in food processor and mix until smooth. Serve with bagels or vegetables.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Add all ingredients and serve.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: do nothing cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl with spoon and pour into prepared pan 9 x 13 inches.
Bake 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream
margarine and sugar;
add eggs and vanilla, then dry ingredients.
Add
oats
minute), raisins and nuts if desired. Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.

title: microwave meat loaf
directions: Mix together.
Put in microwave or glass loaf pan.
Cook on High 7 to 9 minutes; drain and turn.
Cook on High 7 to 9 minutes. Very good.

title: party sized baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger and skim off fat.
Add onion, celery and green pepper; saute until glazed.
Dump everything into a small roasting pan and bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: overnight dill pickles
directions: Bring the ingredients to a boil and let cool.
Spear 8 cucumbers and place in a gallon jar with dill and 2 cloves of garlic.
Pour cool liquid over cucumbers in the jar.
Put in refrigerator until the next day.
Pickles are ready to eat.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake in an unbaked pie shell at 375° for 40-45 mins.

title: crazy crust pie
directions: Melt margarine in a dish in the oven.
While margarine is melting, mix flour and sugar together in another bowl; then add milk, mixing until smooth.
Pour this mixture into melted margarine dish.
Do not stir.
Then spoon your choice of fruit or pie filling on.
Cook at 325° until done.
Simple but great.

title: diet punch
directions: Mix up Kool-Aids with 1 1/2 quarts of water each.
Add orange juice.
Stir well as Kool-Aid clumps if not dissolved well.
Add 1 liter of diet 7-Up.
An ice ring may be made ahead of time with sugar-free Kool-Aid.

title: overnight french toast cut-outs
directions: Spread butter evenly over bottom of jelly roll pan.
Cut centers out of bread with 2-inch cookie cutters.
Arrange bread and cut-outs in single layer
in pan.
Whisk eggs, milk, vanilla, sugar and salt in bowl.
Pour over bread, tilting pan to spread liquid in an even layer.
Refrigerate covered overnight.
To cook, preheat oven to 425°; uncover and bake for 10 minutes.
Flip toast over and bake until browned.

title: pumpkin tea bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in a tube pan or 2 loaf pans at 350°.
The loaf pans take about 45 minutes and the tube pan about 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: hearty beef goulash soup
directions: Dice potatoes; coarsely chop onion.
Warm oil in large saucepan; saute onion and garlic for 1 to 2 minutes.
Crumble ground beef into pan and brown; drain off grease.
Add tomato juice, broth, paprika, pepper and potatoes.
Bring to boil, reduce heat to medium-low, cover and simmer for 10 minutes; stir occasionally.
Dice peppers.
Stir peppers into soup and cook until potatoes are tender, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: tuna-macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package and boil eggs.
Finely chop celery, onions and eggs.
Add all ingredients together with enough mayonnaise to suit personal taste.
(Garnish with paprika).

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Dip will keep in the refrigerator for up to a month.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in 3-quart or larger saucepan.
Add milk and bring to boil.
Don't stir this mixture too much, just enough to get sugar/cocoa dissolved.
Boil for 8 minutes, no longer, no shorter.
Stir only 5 or 6 times during this 8 minutes, stirring from the bottom up.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and butter, stirring until creamy.
Pour into buttered jelly roll pan or other buttered dish.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Mix everything together.
Drop teaspoonfuls of batter onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: icebox cookies
directions: Cream lard, butter and sugars.
Add eggs.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into about 5 long rolls.
Wrap in wax paper and refrigerate overnight.
Slice with sharp knife. Bake on lightly greased baking sheets at 350°.

title: pineapple marshmallow salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Combine sugar, salt and flour in saucepan.
Add egg; blend thoroughly.
Stir in pineapple juice,
cook, stirring constantly, until thick and smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice and peel.
Cover and chill.
Whip the cream stiff and fold into pineapple mixture.
Fold in marshmallows and crushed pineapple.
If desired, 1/4 cup maraschino cherries may be added.
Serve in lettuce cups; garnish with watercress. Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken alfredo and fettuccine
directions: Boil chicken until tender and break into pieces. Drain off chicken broth, saving 1 cup to add back to get the consistency you desire. Add other ingredients and simmer. Serve over noodles.

title: apple cider cheesecake
directions: Spread pie filling on bottom of pie crust. In a large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sour cream and spiced cider; mix until fluffy. Beat in thawed whipped topping. Pour over apple filling and refrigerate. Crush granola bar and sprinkle on top just before serving. Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix in very large bowl.
Use 1/2 to 1/3 cup of the mix with water in cup.
Heat and drink.

title: cherry fruit salad
directions: Mix together first 3 ingredients.
Fold in last 3.
Chill until firm.

title: cheese bread
directions: Stir together water, dry milk, sugar, salt and yeast.
Let stand to dissolve, about 1 minute.
Add cheese and 1 cup flour. Beat until blended.
Add 2 cups flour and blend.
Add 1 cup flour and blend.
Knead 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Knead until smooth; add flour as necessary.
Place in bowl and cover. Let stand.
Punch down after bread doubles in size.
Knead and form into loaves.
Put into loaf pans and cover; let rise.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: yam crunch
directions: Combine yams, 1 stick butter, sugar, milk and eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: strawberry preserves
directions: Boil 5 cups sugar.
Add water until it spins a thread.
Add berries.
Bring to a boil (rolling) for 4 minutes.
Add 4 cups sugar and bring to a boil again for 4 minutes.
Stir and skim off foam.
Pour into shallow pan.
Stir occasionally and leave overnight.
Put in jars and seal.

title: dijon basil vinaigrette
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients well with a wire whisk.
Add olive oil.
Beat well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat well until all are combined.
Stir in pasta salad.

title: pineapple-coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add sugar gradually and mix thoroughly. Melt, then add butter, pineapple (without draining) and coconut. Pour mixture into unbaked pie crust and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes two pies.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Put beans in bottom of a 6 x 12-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with garlic salt.
Mix soup and sour cream and pour over beans. Spread shredded or sliced cheese on top, then top with Durkee onions.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° until onions are brown, about 30 minutes.

title: cake decorating icing
directions: Put shortening in mixing bowl.
Gradually add sugar.
As mixture starts to stiffen, add portions of the milk, one tablespoon at a time until a smooth consistency is obtained.
Add salt, vanilla, almond and butter flavorings.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Put batter into greased and floured tube pan or bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and rinse with cold water. Add vegetables and toss to mix. Mix honey, dressing, cheese and salt. Pour over spaghetti. Stir. Let sit in fridge overnight.

title: banana cake
directions: Place shortening in bowl. Sift in flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Mix. Add 1/3 cup buttermilk and 2 eggs.
Mix 2 more minutes. Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan or two 9 x 1 1/2-inch pans, greased.
Cool.
Remove from pan and frost.
Sour cream or cream cheese frostings are very good.

title: baked eggs
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with the bread slices (crusts removed). Butter bottom sides of bread.
Cover bread with the cheese and meat.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard together; pour over top.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, 1 hour at 350°.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix together and refrigerate. Makes 1 quart.

title: family favorite chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour two 9-inch pans.
Cream butter, shortening, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy; blend in eggs.
Combine baking soda, cocoa, flour, baking powder and salt in bowl; add alternately with milk to batter.
Blend well.
Pour into prepared pans; bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans and cool on wire racks.
Frost with favorite frosting.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Wash and peel cucumbers.
Slice very thin; salt to taste.
Let sit for 15 minutes.
Pour off excess water.
Mix remaining ingredients with cucumbers.
Chill if you like.

title: rye bread filling
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Best if made the night before.
Next day, hollow rye bread, cube.
Fill hollow bread.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a graham cracker crust; chill in freezer.

title: chicken and rice with mushrooms
directions: Batter and fry chicken in oil seasoned with garlic powder. Remove chicken from pan.
Drain grease from pan.
Add soup and mushrooms to pan.
Place chicken on top of soup and mushroom mixture and cook until thick.
Serve and enjoy.

title: all in one casserole
directions: Place cabbage in greased baking dish.
Brown beef and onions. Stir in rice; place over cabbage.
Combine soup and water; pour over top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pasta frola
directions: Cream softened butter and sugar; add yolks, vanilla and flour. Roll out on ungreased cookie sheet (10 x 15-inch).
Bake for 1 hour.
Halfway through cooking take out and cut in 2-inch squares and return to oven and bake until done.
Bake 1 hour at 275°.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and flour pan.
Blend ingredients in large bowl and beat at medium speed for 2 minutes. Cake is done when toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: tangy blue cheese whip
directions: Combine cream, Blue cheese, basil and garlic salt in small mixer bowl.
Beat until mixture thickens.
Fold in almonds. Serve dip sprinkled with additional almonds, with fruit and vegetables.

title: layered salad
directions: Wash and tear lettuce and fill salad bowl at least 3/4 full. (May use iceberg, Romaine and/or spinach as lettuce.)
I like to use a combination of all 3 best.

title: cinnamon fried apples
directions: In large skillet, over medium heat, melt butter.
Add apples, brown sugar and lemon juice; toss gently.

title: egg and potato salad
directions: Mix potatoes, onion and salt.
Marinate in French dressing. Then chill in refrigerator.

title: chocolate chippers
directions: Cream together the shortening, sugars, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Thoroughly stir together the flour, salt and baking soda; stir into creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Stir in chocolate and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes. Immediately remove from cookie sheet to cool.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: wedding punch
directions: Combine fruit juices and Hawaiian punch; freeze.
Thaw mixture in ginger ale.
Dissolve Kool-Aid and sugar in 1 gallon of water; add to punch.

title: date nut bread
directions: Soak dates in water.
Cream egg, vanilla, sugar and butter. Blend in mixer.
Bake 60 minutes at 350°.

title: leek and fennel chowder with smoked salmon
directions: Trim and discard root ends and coarse tops from leeks. cut leeks in half lengthwise and rinse under running water, flipping layers to flush out grit. Drain and thinly slice crosswise. Rinse fennel; trim off and discard roots and stalks. Reserve 2 to 3 feathery sprigs for garnish. Finely chop enough tops to equal 3 tablespoons and set aside. Throw out rest of feathery tops. In a bowl, mix chopped fennel and chives; cover and chill. Chop fennel heads. Melt butter in 6 to 8-quart pan. Add leeks and chopped fennel heads; cover and stir until limp, about 10 to 12 minutes. Add broth and bay leaf to pan. Bring to a boil. Scrub and slice potatoes; add to pan. Return to simmer 15 to 20 minutes until potatoes are tender. Cube smoked salmon and put in bowl. In a separate bowl, whisk milk, flour, salt and pepper until smooth. Add to potato mixture and heat to boiling. Garnish with fennel sprigs and salmon. Serve.

title: orange fluff jello
directions: Put all 3 packages of dry mix into medium pan (puddings and jello) with 2 cups water.
Let set for 5 minutes.
Then bring to a rolling boil, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Add undrained mandarin oranges and juice.
Mix then with the Cool Whip, folding all together.
Refrigerate covered.

title: three fruit punch
directions: Thaw concentrates.
Combine lemonade concentrate, orange juice concentrate and pineapple juice in a large container.
Dissolve sugar in 1/2 cup water.
Add sugar and 11 cups water to juices. Mix well.
Add ginger ale just before serving time; mix gently. Pour over ice in punch bowl.
Ladle into punch cups.

title: cherry jubilee dessert
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple.
Sprinkle package of white cake mix over top; distribute evenly.
Melt margarine in water and pour over top of cake mix.
Top with nuts.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serve with whipped cream or ice cream, if desired.

title: baked barbecued pork chops
directions: Place meat in baking dish and set aside.
Combine butter and onion and cook until onion is light brown.
Add remaining ingredients and bring mixture to a boil.
Pour over meat in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Add 1 cup chopped pecans and mix.
Refrigerate until firm and shape into ball.
Roll in remaining pecans before serving.
Garnish as desired.
Serve with crackers.

title: meat loaf with creole sauce
directions: In a bowl, combine all the ingredients for the meat loaf.
Mix and blend well to a smooth consistency.
Place meat in a greased loaf pan.
Smooth top.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until meat loaf is done.
In the meantime, prepare sauce.

title: white layer cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add one egg yolk at the time.
Beat for about 4 minutes.
Add flavoring and milk with flour.
Beat egg whites and add in last.
Pour in 3 cake pans after spraying with Pam.

title: creamy lemon meringue pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In mixing bowl, beat egg yolks; add milk and lemon juice.
Pour into crust.
In mixer bowl, beat egg whites with cream of tartar to soft peaks.
Gradually add sugar; beat until stiff.
Spread on pie; seal to edge.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool. Chill.

title: pineapple lemon punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in punch bowl, adding ginger ale just before serving.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serve with mini party bread or crackers.

title: grits casserole
directions: Brown sausage, bell pepper and onion; drain.
Grease casserole dish with margarine.
Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken in water with salt, pepper, poultry seasoning and bay leaf.
Boil until tender.
Set aside to cool.
Save broth to cook spaghetti in.
Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Add mushrooms (juice too), all 3 cans of soup, chunk up the Velveeta and drop in mixture; stir until cheese melts.
Remove from heat. Cook spaghetti in broth from chicken.
Mix cooked spaghetti into other mixture.
Heat on stove top and serve.

title: pico de gallo
directions: First wash cilantro; let drain.
Dice the onion, tomatoes and jalapenos.
(Make sure your tomatoes are not from stores, the taste is 100% better when bought from a fruit stand or home grown.)
Next take only 1/2 of the cilantro bunch and chop it, do not use the stem, only the leaves.
Mix all ingredients; add salt to taste.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine all veggies in bowl.
Add salt and pepper.
Put vinegar, sugar and oil in a pan.
Bring to a boil, then let cool. Pour over veggies and refrigerate overnight.

title: spinach supreme
directions: Cook spinach
according to package directions and drain thoroughly.
Melt
butter, add spinach, soup, onion and garlic cheese.
Mix well
over
medium heat until all ingredients are combined and cheese
is melted.
Stir in almonds.
Pour into a buttered 3-quart
casserole.
Bake, covered 20 minutes at 350° or until
bubbly.
Just
before
serving,
garnish with sesame seeds. Can be
prepared ahead and refrigerated and heated for 40 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: can't fail cookies
directions: In a small bowl, mix well the flour and 2 tablespoons brown sugar.
With fingers, work in 1/2 cup butter until dough begins to hold together.
Press in bottom of a greased 9-inch square pan. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: plum cake
directions: Preheat oven at 325°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Mix well.
Bake for 1 hour, or until done.
Glaze with lemon juice and confectioners sugar.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add 1 egg at a time; beat after each one.
Add the soda in 1/2 cup buttermilk.
Add other ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Use Bundt pan.

title: spiced apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Combine cake mix, eggs and oil in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed with mixer for 2 minutes.
Stir in apples, nuts and raisins. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool completely.
Serves 12 to 16. Frost with Duncan Hines vanilla frosting.

title: grandma's famous chocolate brownies
directions: Heat margarine and 1 cup of chocolate chips in 3-quart saucepan over low heat until melted.
Stir in remaining chips and rest of ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cool completely and cut into bars.
Makes 36 bars.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Arrange tomatoes in a buttered 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Saute celery and onion in butter for 2 minutes.
Stir in seasons. Set aside 1/4 cup celery mixture; spoon remainder over tomatoes. Combine reserved celery mixture and croutons.
Tossing gently, spoon over tomatoes.
Cover; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: turkey oriental
directions: In a greased casserole dish place a layer of vegetables (drained), grated onion and turkey.
Repeat.
Mix soup with 3 tablespoons vinegar, soy sauce and curry and pour over casserole. Cover with crumbs.
Bake at 375° until bubbly and browned.

title: chocolate fudge(foolproof)
directions: In a heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chips with sweetened condensed milk.
Remove from heat; stir in remaining ingredients. Stir until chips are melted.
Spread evenly into greased 8-inch square pan.
Chill 2 to 3 hours or until firm.
Cut into squares and store, loosely covered, at room temperature.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Cut up bananas in pineapple juice.
Cover and let sit for 20 minutes.
Drain and cut peaches into
chunks. Drain cherries and cut in half.
Mix fruit into glaze.
Add drained bananas last.

title: escalloped turkey
directions: Cook celery in water until just tender.
Pour melted butter over toast cubes.
Combine water from celery with enough milk to make 2 cups liquid.
Cook the butter and flour over low heat until bubbly.
Add the 2 cups of liquid, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add seasoning.
Arrange turkey and celery in a layer over 1/2 the toast cubes in casserole dish.
Pour sauce over this and top with remaining toast cubes and press down.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt butter. Add cumin, mustard, picante sauce and flour; stir until smooth. Then add cheese and milk.

title: speedy meatballs
directions: Bake meatballs at 350° on a cookie sheet until done.
Melt the jelly; add ketchup and mustard.
Pour over meatballs.
Heat and serve.
(Good as a potluck dish; put in a slow cooker.)

title: creamed corn casserole
directions: Slice squash or peeled eggplant in about 1/2-inch slices. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Dredge both sides in self-rising flour.
Drop in hot oil or bacon drippings in large frying pan. Cook both sides until brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: hot curried fruit
directions: Mix and pour over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: tomato pie
directions: Bake frozen pie shell 5 to 7 minutes.
Place tomatoes in bottom of pie shell; top with crumbled bacon.
Combine cheese and mayonnaise; pour over tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into pie shell. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Boil just until tender and drain. Slice hard-boiled eggs.
Layer potatoes, bacon, egg and onion in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Pour sauce over mixture and bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Combine milk, soup, pepper and 1/2 of can of French fried onions.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes or heated.
Top with remaining 1/2 can French fried onions.
Bake uncovered 5 minutes or onions are brown.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Melt margarine; mix with eggs and pineapple.
Add sugar and flour.
Tear bread up; press into mixture.
Bake in casserole dish at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil potatoes until soft; drain.
Add milk and onion.
Add hot liquid.
Make white sauce.
Cook five minutes.
Add parsley just before serving.

title: tuna casserole
directions: In buttered 2 or 3-quart casserole dish, mix all ingredients well.
Cover with 1/2 cup "more" shredded cheese.
Refrigerate immediately.
Remove after 1 or more hours.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes (45 minutes to 1 hour is better).

title: forgotten dessert
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Beat egg whites and salt until foamy. Add cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff, then add sugar, about 1 tablespoon at a time, and vanilla.
Beat well.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in oven, turn off heat and go to bed!
Do not peek!

title: pineapple ice
directions: Freeze first 3 ingredients to mushy 1/2 to 1 hour.
Add pineapple juice and freeze to mushy 1/2 hour.
Fold in egg whites and refreeze.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour.

title: kindergarten room 3 applesauce(1993-1994 voted number 4)
directions: Chop apples.
Boil in 1/2-inch water.
Add honey; boil and stir.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and eat.

title: yellow rice and chicken
directions: Do not flour chicken.
Fry chicken in oil, then fry onion and garlic until tender.
Add tomatoes and broth.
Boil for 5 minutes in the pot; add bay leaf, salt, rice, food coloring and green pepper.
Blend and place in a long baking dish.
Bake for 20 minutes or until rice is tender and has absorbed moisture. Garnish with peas and pimento, if desired.
Yields 6 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs;
add sugar, syrup, butter, vanilla and salt. Add pecans.
Pour in pastry shells.
Bake at 300° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs together.
Mix in the milk, nutmeg, vanilla and salt.
Then slowly add and mix in the flour.

title: baked squash
directions: Cook squash in salted water; drain and mash.
Add remaining ingredients except margarine holding back stuffing.
Line 2-quart casserole with half of stuffing that has been mixed with 1 stick melted margarine.
Fill with squash mixture and then sprinkle remaining 1/2 of stuffing on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: red velvet cake("a pretty cake for christmas")
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients in order listed; mix thoroughly.
Grease and flour layer cake pans. Spread in pans.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 minutes or until cake tests done.
Remove from pan; let cool.
(I use only one can of cherry pie or strawberry pie filling between layers as well as filling and frosting following.)

title: pineapple orange carrot jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O in hot water, add cold water and pineapple and grated carrots; mix and put in refrigerator until set.
Unmold on a bed of lettuce or serve from bowl.
Good with all kinds of meals and easy to make at camp.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Cut asparagus in 1-inch pieces.
Mix vegetables and soup, put in a casserole dish, top with cheese and add canned onion rings. Bake at 400° for about 25 to 30 minutes, or until firm and brown.

title: holiday fruit ball
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix 1 cup powdered sugar until well blended. Add each ingredient separately and mix well. After all ingredients are mixed, top with chopped pecans

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix into stiff dough.
Form into small balls.
Flatten with bottom of glass or fork.
Place without touching on cookie sheet and bake on middle rack at 375°.

title: egg casserole
directions: Mix thoroughly and refrigerate overnight in a 13 x 9-inch glass pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli; drain well and place in greased 10 x 10-inch casserole dish.
Layer chicken on top of broccoli.
Combine next 4 ingredients and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle with cheese. Sprinkle cracker crumbs over all.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cut in shortening.
Set aside.
Combine milk and sweet potatoes.
Add to flour mixture and stir quickly.
Knead lightly using as little flour on board as possible.
Roll out to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with floured cutter.
Place on a greased baking sheet and bake in a preheated 475° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 25 biscuits.

title: yum yum salad
directions: Dissolve Jello in hot water.
Add cottage cheese, pineapple, milk and mayonnaise.
Mix well; stir in nuts.
Pour into mold; chill until firm.

title: hawaiian cooler
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in pitcher.
Mix well.
Pour over ice into tall glasses. Garnish with strawberry-pineapple kabobs. Yields 8 servings.

title: fried corn
directions: In a large frying pan, fry bacon until crisp.
Put corn into hot grease.
Stir corn, do not let it burn.
Fry on medium. Crumble bacon into corn.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook about 45 minutes until grease has cooked out.
Serve hot.

title: lime party salad
directions: Melt in top of a double boiler:
1/4 pound miniature marshmallows (about 16).
Pour hot mixture over jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Then stir in cream cheese.
Add pineapple.
Cool. Blend in whipping cream and mayonnaise.

title: antique show corn chowder
directions: In a
6 or 8-quart kettle, saute the bacon until crisp. Remove from pan and drain on paper towels.
Remove all but 1/2 cup drippings from pan.
In the drippings, saute the onion until tender, about 5 minutes.
Add potatoes and water; bring to a boil and cook, covered, until potatoes are tender, about 10 or 15 minutes.
Add corn and milk; heat gently.
Add butter, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with bacon pieces when serving.
Makes 5 1/2 quarts or about 25 servings.

title: homemade turtle candy
directions: Melt 1/2 package of almond bark in double boiler.
Arrange 3 pecans in a cluster on a greased cookie sheet.
Place unwrapped caramel on each cluster of 3 or more pecans.
Place in oven at 325°, just until caramel begins to soften.
Remove from oven and transfer to wax paper.
Cool.
Place with a spoon melted bark on each cluster.
Cool.
Store in a tin.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Sift together flour, ginger, cloves, nutmeg and allspice.
Work shortening in a bowl until creamy.
Add sugar and beat until well blended.
Combine salt, water and rum; stir to dissolve salt.
Stir soda into molasses and combine with water mixture.
Add liquid mixture and sifted dry ingredients alternately to shortening mixture.
Mix well after each addition.
Cover and chill overnight. Heat oven to 375°.
Roll a small portion of dough at a time.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake.

title: perfect custard pie
directions: Prepare and bake pie shell; let cool completely.
Meanwhile, preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch pie plate.
Beat eggs slightly, then add remaining ingredients and beat until well mixed.
Pour into prepared pie plate; set plate in pan of cold water.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes, or until silver knife inserted 1 inch from edge of filling comes out clean.
The center may look a bit soft, but it will set as custard cools.
When filling is completely cool, loosen from pie plate by carefully running a small spatula around edge and shaking plate gently.
Holding custard just above far rim of pastry shell, carefully slip it into shell.

title: pork chops-n-potato bake
directions: Brown pork chops in lightly greased skillet.
Sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Combine soup, milk, sour cream, salt and pepper. Stir in potatoes.
Layer the pork chops on top of potatoes and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
After baking, set the pork chops to the side and add the cheese and the French fried onions to the top of the potatoes.
Bake the potatoes for five more minutes until cheese is melted.
Serve with the pork chops.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix cherries and pineapple.
Pour in baking dish (13 x 9-inch).
Sprinkle with 1/2 box of yellow cake mix on top of fruit.
Cut stick of oleo on top of cake mix.
Spread pecans on top.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes or until cake mix is brown.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In medium bowl, combine pretzels, butter and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Press on bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch cake pan.
Bake 8 minutes.
Cool.

title: frozen orange pie
directions: Place orange juice
in	large
bowl.
Beat
30 seconds. Add ice cream
and
blend.
Fold
in
whip
cream.
Beat until smooth. Freeze, if necessary, until the mixture mounds. Spoon into pie crust and freeze until firm, at least 4 hours.
Store any leftovers in the freezer.

title: pistachio jello
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cherries, together.
Dot with cherries for color.
Chill and serve.

title: one pan meal
directions: Pour water in roasting pan with rack.
Place chicken in center of rack.
Place the first 4 vegetables around chicken.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and butter or dot with margarine (saving enough to top cabbage).
Place cabbage leaves over the top of meat and vegetables.
Sprinkle with butter or dot with remaining margarine. Put lid on pan; cook on medium heat for 30 to 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: In a saucepan, blend soup, 1/2 cup water and cheese.
Heat slowly until cheese melts. Blend in remaining ingredients.
Serves 4.
Has approximately 6 grams fat per serving.

title: old fashioned potatoes with thickening
directions: Peel potatoes and quarter (scrape new potatoes and leave whole).
Add water, butter, salt and pepper.
Bring to a rolling boil and reduce heat to simmer.
Cook about 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Remove from heat.
In small bowl, mix cornstarch with milk.
Pour over potatoes and stir well.
Return to medium heat and cook until the liquid thickens.
Stir frequently.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: mexican spaghetti
directions: Saute meat, onion, pepper, salt and garlic powder. Add taco seasoning, tomato sauce, water and mushroom soup.
Simmer; add tomato juice if needed. Cook 1 small package spaghetti (broken). Combine sauce and spaghetti in 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix in cheese. Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: sugarless pumpkin custard
directions: Combine pumpkin, salt and spices. Add remaining ingredients. Pour into 9 custard cups or an 8-inch square pan. Set in a shallow pan and fill pan to 1 inch with hot water. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until a knife when inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: sally's grape leaf pickles
directions: Note:
Need one 3 gallon stone crock (open top).

title: golden pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend all ingredients in a large bowl; beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan, 10-inch or fluted, at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes, until center springs back when touched lightly.
Cool right side up in pan for 25 minutes, then invert onto plate.

title: chinese-style vegetables
directions: Prepare 3 cups finely shredded cabbage.
Heat shortening in 10-inch skillet until melted.
Stir in cabbage, celery, green pepper and onion.
Cover and cook over medium heat, stirring several times, until vegetables are tender, about 5 minutes. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: peter reuben's mother's chocolate cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding mix, eggs and milk by hand until smooth. Add chocolate chips.
Bake in 2 greased and lightly floured loaf pans at 350° for 50 minutes or until a soft touch bounces back. Cool 10 minutes and remove from pans.
Makes 2 loaf cakes.

title: italian rice
directions: In saucepan, heat oil with 3 tablespoons butter.
Add onion and saute over low heat until soft, but not brown, about 5 minutes.
Add garlic and cook about 30 seconds.
Stir in rice and cook, stirring frequently, until rice begins to turn yellow.
Do not allow rice to brown.
Add wine and simmer until wine has evaporated.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups broth.
Cover and cook over low heat until liquid is absorbed, about 10 minutes.
Add remaining broth.
Stir gently with fork.
Cover again and cook 15 minutes or until rice is tender.
Then stir in Parmesan and remaining butter.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats and oleo.
Let stand for 20 minutes.
Use 3 minute oats.
Add sugars, eggs, cinnamon, flour, soda, salt and nutmeg.
Bake 35 minutes at 350° in long flat pot.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Pour 1 cup rice in bottom of glass baking dish.
Pour cream of mushroom and 2 cans of water over rice.
Add dry onion soup mix. Stir.
Lay chicken in dish and salt and pepper and put butter on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered.
Uncover and cook 30 more minutes.

title: saucy spareribs
directions: In a large baking dish, combine all ingredients except the ribs.
Add ribs and cover and marinate in the refrigerator, turning occasionally at least 3 hours.
Preheat oven to 350°. Remove ribs and reserve marinade.
Place ribs on a rack in foil-lined pan.
Bake 1 1/4 hours, turning and basting until done.

title: gelatin pizza
directions: You will need a 12-inch pizza pan with 1/2-inch sides.

title: kraut relish
directions: Heat sugar and vinegar until sugar is dissolved; cool. Combine undrained sauerkraut, celery, green pepper, onion and pimiento; combine with vinegar mixture.
Chill.
Serves 4 cups.

title: fancy meat loaf roll
directions: In a bowl, combine ground beef, bread crumbs, egg, garlic powder and salt.
Mix well.
On wax paper, pat meat mixture into a 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Combine the spices and sprinkle over meat. Sprinkle onion, cheese and mushrooms over meat.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Pour tomato sauce over roll and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot cross buns
directions: Dissolve yeast and 2 tablespoons sugar in lukewarm milk.
Add 3 1/4 cups flour to make sponge.
Beat until smooth.
Cover and let rise until light in a warm place away from draft (approximately 1 hour).
Add butter and sugar creamed, eggs well beaten, raisins which have been floured, rest of flour or enough to make a moderately soft dough and salt.
Turn on board, knead lightly and place in greased bowl.
Cover and set aside in warm place until double in bulk, which should be in about 2 hours.

title: preacher cookies
directions: In large bowl, mix well sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa. Pour mixture in a saucepan and bring to a boil for about 1/2 minute.
Remove from stove.
Add oatmeal, raisins, peanut butter and vanilla flavoring.
Cook mixture once again and remove from stove once it comes to a boil.
Stir together and drop on wax paper.
Allow 15 to 20 minutes to cool.

title: caramel dip
directions: Mix all ingredients; chill.
Serve with fruit slices.

title: mozzarella loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix meat, bread crumbs, eggs, onions and seasonings into a firm ball.
On waxed paper, press ball into a rectangle approximately 1 1/2 inches thick.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 cups cheese on top of meat.
Starting at one end, roll rectangle into a jelly roll, making sure you pinch ends closed.
Place in baking dish or roasting pan and cover with marinara sauce.
Bake 1 1/2 hours, adding remainder of cheese to top 5 minutes before removing from oven.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes.
Slice and serve.

title: green bean salad
directions: Steam the beans until just crisp-tender, about 3 or 4 minutes. While the beans steam, place the oil in a small skillet with sunflower seeds.
Stir the seeds over medium heat until they are golden brown.
Do not overcook.
Remove from heat.

title: cheesy potato soup
directions: Put cut-up vegetables in large pot.
Add 3 quarts water and seasonings; cook for 45 minutes.
Add instant potatoes and Velveeta cheese.
Be sure and rinse your cut up vegetables several times before you add your 3 quarts water.

title: hungarian gulyas(ground beef version)
directions: Grease casserole.
Make a layer (use 1/2 of all ingredients) of potatoes, onion, beef, tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Repeat as above ending with tomatoes on top layer.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour until potatoes are done.
Serves 4.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in airtight container.
To serve:
Combine 1/3 cup dry mix to 1 cup boiling water.
Makes 4 quarts dry mix.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: In skillet, cook meat until brown.
Drain off excess fat. Separate crescent dough into 8 triangles.
Place on an ungreased 12-inch pizza pan with points to center.
Press over bottom and up sides to form a crust; seal perforations.
Spoon meat over crust. Sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with cheese.
In a bowl, beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over crust.
Sprinkle Parmesan over all.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix well and heat in a medium oven for 30 minutes or until heated through.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Cut franks lengthwise and insert cheese.
Wrap biscuits around franks.
Bake according to directions for biscuits.

title: corn spoon bread
directions: Mix well.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch glass pan.
Bake at 325° until firm, about 30 minutes.

title: cocktail wiener wraps
directions: Cut bacon slices into 2 pieces and wrap a cocktail wiener in each 1/2 slice.
Secure with a toothpick and place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle brown sugar over top of wieners.
Cook in 350° oven until bacon browns.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni then drain.
Add all other ingredients; mix well.
Add ingredients in more or less amounts to suit taste. Makes 6 servings.

title: mulled cider
directions: Mix all ingredients except lemon slices in a saucepan.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Remove spices.
Serve hot garnished with lemon slices.
Makes 8 servings, about 1/2 cup each.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well and form into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. (You do not have to precook sausage.)

title: tortilla sauce
directions: Crush tomatoes; chop onions
and peppers.
Cook in pan for 30 minutes.
Eat with tortilla chips.

title: stuffed cabbage leaves
directions: Sauce:
Heat diced celery, onions and carrots in frying pan for a few minutes (keep crispy).
Put in blender and pulse until finely chopped.
Pour in pan and add brown sugar, tomato juice, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and ginger.
Cook until sugar melts (set aside).

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix together.
Optional additions:
corn and ham, green peppers or mushrooms.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes (done when knife stuck in middle comes out clean).

title: strawberry cream dessert(prep: 15 minutes plus refrigerating)
directions: Trim 3/4-inch from ends of ladyfingers; place ends on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan. Stand remaining ladyfingers around side of pan with cut sides facing in. Reserve 2 strawberries for garnish; mash remaining strawberries.

title: sunshine tuna bake
directions: In a saucepan, cook vegetables in margarine until tender. Combine with soup, milk, macaroni, tomato and tuna in a 1 1/2-quart buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: russian dressing
directions: Whirl the first six ingredients in blender.
Beat in salad oil and vinegar while blender is running.

title: chocolate cake with boiled frosting
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease and flour a 13 x 9 pan. Sift together the first 5 ingredients, then add to the rest of the ingredients. Beat ingredients for 4 minutes, then pour into pan and bake for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken-fried round steak
directions: Pound steak thoroughly. Dip into egg mixed with milk, then into crumbs or flour. Brown on both sides in hot fat.
Season. Cover and cook over very low heat 45 minutes to 60 minutes. Serves 6.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain away fat.
Add 6 cups of water, onions and celery.
Bring to a boil.
Add onion soup mix and bouillon cubes.
Crush, by hand, whole tomatoes.
Add to soup along with the juice.
Add frozen vegetables and pasta.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Continue to boil until veggies and celery are tender. Let simmer on low heat and then serve.

title: pizza potatoes
directions: Skin, slice and boil potatoes.
Drain and cool a few minutes. Preheat oven to 400°.
Put potatoes into lightly greased glass baking dish.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch pan, melt butter.
Sprinkle crumbs (crushed vanilla wafers) over butter.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients.
Press down gently.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Let cool; cut into squares.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Best when refrigerated 24 hours before serving, so as to marinate.
Stir at least once.

title: chocolate syrup cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add flour and baking powder, sifted together, and blend in chocolate syrup.
Add 3/4 cup chopped walnuts.
Place in a greased baking dish and bake at 325° to 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: joy's rocky road cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and brown sugar; then add eggs and vanilla. Sift together dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop golf ball sized spoonfuls 2 inches apart on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes, no longer.
Remove from sheet to cool.

title: snowball cookies
directions: Cream margarine, powdered sugar and vanilla together.
Add flour, salt and nuts.
Put in refrigerator to chill; roll into walnut size balls.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
While hot, roll in powdered sugar.
Cool.
Roll in plain sugar.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/4 cup sugar to whites after stiff.
Beat yolks, add 1/2 cup sugar while beating.
Mix whites and yolks together.
Stir in milk.
Slowly pour over a block of vanilla ice cream.
(Sprinkle nutmeg over top.)

title: maw's cereal cookies
directions: Beat shortening, sugar, egg, milk and vanilla together until creamy.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture; blend well.
Stir in nuts, dates and cereal.
Drop by teaspoonful on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: southwest chicken
directions: Marinate chicken breast for 1 hour.
Grill chicken, when done, place 1 slice of cheese on chicken, remove when melted.
Top with chopped tomatoes and scallions.

title: granny gibbs' lye soap
directions: In granite dishpan, put the water.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Let cool to 80°.
Then weigh 10 pounds of fat, melted and strained through a cloth.
Heat to 100°.
Pour fat very slowly into 80° lye solution, stirring all the time you are pouring.
Stir until it is the consistency of nice, thick cream.
Stand until it begins to harden, then cut into bars.
Put in boxes.
Cover with cloth.
The longer it stays, the whiter it gets and the better it performs.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients
and place in baking dish.
Top with strips of bacon.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hot fudge cake
directions: After cake is removed from oven, while hot, punch holes in cake with wooden spoon handle.
Pour cream in over cake.
Then pour caramel topping over cake.
Chill in refrigerator.
After cake has cooled, top with Cool Whip.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add egg yolks one at a time and beat well.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with buttermilk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Make 4 layers and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruited ham salad
directions: In a small mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except lettuce and tomato. Stir until thoroughly blended.

title: silver queen corn pudding
directions: Position knife blade in food processor bowl.
Add corn and pulse until finely chopped.
Place in colander; drain 1 hour. Combine corn and remaining ingredients; stir well.
Pour corn mixture into ungreased 2-quart casserole.
Bake uncovered at 325° for 1 hour and 45 minutes or until set.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Stew chicken in stock pot for one hour.
Cut up carrots, onion and stew with chicken.
Take chicken out of stock pot and cool it in refrigerator.
When cooled, de-bone the chicken and put back into the stock pot with vegetables.

title: m&m cookies
